column7: Tentative Description (Note: each description was not provided by the artists, but was generated using artificial intelligence with human supervision, and is still open to different interpretations).

Two blue whales intertwined, suspended from a large draped fabric beach towel, which is white with bold red stripes. The fabric is hung on an oversized wooden hanger, which is affixed to the top edge of the building. Background in beige.

Large watermelon slice against a muted blue background. The watermelon has red pulp contrasting with dark black seeds. The seeds are depicted as if they are being ejected out of the watermelon slice. The slice's green rind fades into its bright red interior, with the white layer acting as a transition between the two. The artist name "Woskerski" appears in the top right corner.

Polar bear, painted in white and light gray, standing on top of a melting ice cap shaped like a human head, rendered in icy blue. The background is dominated by shades of red, with flames rising from the ground below. The flames are depicted in yellows and oranges, contrasting with the cool tones of the polar bear and ice cap.

Underwater scene. At the forefront, a colored koi fish is illustrated with a patchwork of red, yellow, and white scales. Adjacent to the koi, a smaller silver-colored fish. In the middle section, folded paper boat floats atop the water. The underwater background is filled with swirling, dynamic patterns in shades of blue and green. Floating water lilies with yellow centers and round green leaves. (On the artist's website, it's noted that the mural commemorates Japanese immigration to Brazil, starting in 1908. It features three carps, each symbolizing different aspects: one is a traditional Koi, another shaped like origami, and the third resembles the Japanese flag with its coloration. The background includes a reproduction of Claude Monet's "Water Lilies," highlighting the influence of Japanese culture in Brazil. The carp are used to symbolize the resilience and contributions of Japanese immigrants. The mural also portrays a stone skipping on water, representing joy, lightness, and balance, emphasizing the positive impact of immigrants on national culture.)

column3: Matthew and Roxanne Ortiz (Artist Name: Wooden Wave)
column7: A sustainable coastal habitat. A treehouse-like structure with multiple levels is integrated within the trees. The structure is adorned with various green technologies, including solar panels and green roofs. A few of the levels have platforms or terraces that offer panoramic views of the ocean below. At the uppermost part of the structure is an observation tower with a spiral design. Additionally, hanging gardens or planters and various living spaces are apparent. The backdrop features an ocean meeting a golden-hued sky at the horizon.
column9: Graffiti Arts | Mural Art & Consulting LLC © 2022

column3: Matthew and Roxanne Ortiz (Artist Name: Wooden Wave)
column7: A large, intertwined tree with various colorful structures, possibly homes or buildings, perched on its branches. There's a blending of the natural world with human-made structures. On the left side of the tree: waves in varying shades of blue, capturing the movementof the ocean.

column3: Matthew and Roxanne Ortiz (Artist Name: Wooden Wave)
column7: Blend of nature and architecture. Central to the composition is a large, multifaceted structure that appears to be a combination of a treehouse and a ship. This building is equipped with solar panels. A tree with a swing and a platform extends from the left side. Below, a flowing river or body of water, and the foreground has a variety of plants and flowers in multiple colors. A clear sky with a hint of sunset forms the backdrop.

Urban setting capturing daily life in a city environment. On the left, a traditional brick buildings juxtaposed with a large, more modern building labeled "METROPOLITAN" on the right. In the foreground, people are engaged in various activities, from playing soccer to enjoying music and shopping from street vendors. Large flowers and leaves burst forth.

Underwater scene with marine life. In the left, a large fish with a lantern-like organ used to attract prey. Next, another marine creature strapped with urban and industrial items, including a building and a truck. As we move further right, two fish facing each other, with one exhibiting bold, striking colors, and the other having a more pastel hue. (Note: A mural about the defense of the deep ocean).

Underwater with marine life, with several aquatic species: graceful dolphins, a sea turtle, tropical fish, (including clownfish), stingrays, a sailfish, and a whale with bubbles escaping its blowhole. A coral reef extends along the bottom of the mural, housing various colorful corals, fish, and a starfish. Predominant blue; brighter colors of the marine flora and fauna, such as the yellows, oranges, reds, and greens from the reef and the fish.

A trash bin filled with various waste items, ranging from discarded cans with visible brand labels, to crumpled plastic cups, bottle caps, and even a yellow rubber glove. The can's exterior displays a design of wooden planks. Below the trash bin, on the ground, lay more waste items: a crushed can, a bottle cap, and a discarded wrapper or packet. The color palette is dominated by muted tones typical of waste materials—browns, grays, and silvers, with splashes of color from the discarded items like the green bottle cap, the blue label, and the red can.

The mural depicts a large, somber person wearing a golden crown adorned with various symbols and oil company logos, including Shell and BP. The person's face, detailed in grayscale with a serious expression, is shown as they appears to be sucking the resources of the Earth through a straw that extends from the globe they are holding. The globe, filled with water, represents the planet, and the straw symbolizes the exploitation and draining of Earth's resources. To the left, a yellow hand is seen protruding from behind the building, holding a small figure that seems to be bound and manipulated, highlighting the power dynamics between corporations and individuals. The mural uses a palette of gray and black for the figures, with bright yellow for the hand and crown, and green and blue for the Earth. The building's red-bricked windows serve as the backdrop.

column3: Daniela Guerreiro, Nuno Viegas e Élsio Menau
column7: A net filled with fish and various types of plastic waste, such as bottles, cans, and face masks. The background features shades of blue, suggesting the ocean. The predominant colors: various shades of blue, representing the ocean, along with natural colors for the fish and more artificial colors for the plastic waste.

A three-dimensional illusion of a crumpled piece of paper, folded into the shape of an airplane. The design on the paper seems to mimic the lines of a topographical map, with contour lines and markings suggesting mountainous terrain. The colors range from earthy browns to light blues. One side of the paper airplane appears to be burning, with the edges curling and darkened as if they are being consumed by flames. This burning effect is subtle. The background is a light, airy blue, which contrasts with the earthy tones of the paper and the detail of the burning.

A young person playing on the beach, building something with plastic bottles and other trash materials. The background shows a clear blue sky and the sandy beach. The predominant colors are bright blues for the sky, sandy browns for the beach, and various shades of green, blue, and white for the materials.

A water faucet painted to look bit rusty, with a metallic gray color and some blue-green spots where the metal has oxidized. From the faucet, a single drop of water is falling to transform into a small green plant with leaves. The plant appears to be growing out of the water drop. The background of the painting is the plain, earthy wall of the building. Predominant colors are various shades of blue and green for the faucet and plant, with a beige background.

A person in traditional clothing, accompanied by a donkey. Both the person and the donkey seem to be near a rustic building, possibly a stable or an old barn. The backdrop consists of stone walls, an old wooden door, and scattered hay on the ground. There is a sign "Belmont". Dominant colors include earthy tones such as browns and grays, with touches of blue in the person's shirt and yellow in their pants.

column3: Mark Samsonovich - unsure if this is the artist
column4: Warning: Too Much Consumption May Cause Sickness
column7: A person regurgitating a cascade of magazine clippings, advertisements, and brand logos flows out. Above the figure, there's a warning that reads: "TOO MUCH CONSUMPTION MAY CAUSE SICKNESS." The primary colors are muted, such as the gray of the figure and the brown of the brick background. These are contrasted by the colors of the clippings and advertisements

Two individuals. The left figure appears to be passionately shouting or singing into a megaphone. The right figure, on the other hand, is captured in the act of pouring a liquid from a bottle, with the fluid taking on a whimsical shape in mid-air. Dominant hues include shades of blue in the background, bright yellows and reds in the flowers and abstract designs, and contrasting whites, blacks, and greys in the figures themselves.

It features hands performing various activities – from pouring water and holding soil, to holding a basket of plants and a lit bulb – against a backdrop of a sun, mountains, and diverse flora. A noticeable text, "Solar Commons", emphasizes the theme of shared solar resources. It incorporates a variety of bright hues, such as blues, oranges, reds, yellows, and greens.

Face of a person, appearing as if they are submerged halfway in the water. their closed eye and the gentle curve of their nose and lips are seen above the waterline, while the water casts a vibrant blue shade below. The water seems to distort or obscure the part of their face that is submerged. To the right of the mural, there's a detailed, decorative pattern that seems reminiscent of waves or fluid motion, further amplifying the aquatic theme. The upper portion of the mural, showcasing the person's face, is in a monochrome palette. Below their eyes, a blue hue symbolizes the water. The patterns on the right are rendered in a lighter, silvery shade. (Part of the initiative "Hold Water")

A large, transparent glass bottle lying on its side, with a detailed, miniature world contained within it. Inside the bottle, a small island with lush greenery, surrounded by blue ocean waters. On the island, a few structures are visible, likely representing houses or buildings nestled among the greenery. Beneath the island, the ocean scene continues with a large whale swimming near the ocean floor, accompanied by other smaller sea creatures. The ocean is depicted in a range of blue tones. Above the water, the sky is illustrated in a gradient from light blue to a vibrant pink. A large, pink cloud hovers over the island. A small boat is seen floating on the water near the mouth of the bottle. The bottle itself is rendered with intricate detail, showing reflections and highlights that make it appear three-dimensional.

A layered arrangement of marine animals, ascending in a vertical stack. Two large whales, a dolphin, and a polar bear. The whales are stacked on top of each other, their bodies curving and intertwining. At the top of the stack, the polar bear is perched on the uppermost golphin. The animals are rendered in shades of gray with prominent pink, contrasting the pastel blue background. Below the marine creatures, there's a pink strip that appears to represent the surface of the water. Beneath this strip, near the bottom of the mural, there are small silhouetted figures of people.

Blend of land and marine animals intertwined in a vertical cascade. The top features terrestrial animals like lions, bears, and deer. As we move downward, the mural transitions to marine life, including a large whale and a baby elephant perched on its nose. The mural's background shifts from a light blue to a deeper blue. Surrounding the main images are outlines of other animals.The background predominantly features shades of blue. The terrestrial animals are mostly rendered in grays and browns, while the whale has a deep blue-gray hue. A pink stripe splits the mural.

A young individual, seemingly female, with a second face rendered on a mask that they holds above their own. The primary face appears somber, while the mask has eyes gazing upward. The main face features natural tones of browns, while the mask has an orange hue. The backdrop is in shades of blue.

Figures that appear to be influenced by Greco-Roman statues. These figures have contemporary elements such as gas masks and the red cross symbols on their clothing. One figure, with wings like an angel or a classical messenger god, holds an object resembling the SARS-CoV-2 virus. Another figure, seated with a spear, wears a gas mask and also sports a red cross on their garb. Dominant colors: shades of grey, red accents on the cross symbols and certain parts of the figures. The background is white.

A close-up of a person, from a cropped perspective focusing primarily on their upper torso and hands. The person is depicted holding a bouquet of flowers, with the flowers' colors contrasting with the muted palette of the background. On the bottom right side of the artwork, the words "AMOR PROPRIO" (translating to "self-love") are painted. Dominant colors: muted shades of pinks and purples in the person and flowers. Background with hues of red, brown, and olive green.

Close-up of a person's face, where they has a wooden birdhouse atop their head. One side of their face is obscured by a white cloth, and they holds the cloth with their fingers, revealing only their lips and a part of their nose. their lips are prominently painted with a dark shade. The background is a calming shade of turquoise, in contrasts with the wooden texture and color of the birdhouse.

A pair of hands cradling a plant. Dotted rain droplets fall around, nurturing the plant. The background showcases a gradient from a vivid green at the top, transitioning into a sky-blue with representations of leaves and foliage. Bottom right: representations of plants and flowers growing. Dominant colors: green, skin tones in the hands, and blues in the backdrop.

A bear wearing a hat and an orange life vest is seated on a large blue whale. The bear is holding a fork and plate of food, appearing to be dining. The whale is depicted swimming with part of its body submerged and part above water, while the bear sits comfortably atop its back. Behind the bear, there is a refrigerator strapped to its back. Colors: Blue for the whale and background water. The bear has shades of brown and orange. Additional colors include white and light shades for details.
A young person, donning a hoodie, sticking their tongue out playfully, painted in shades of blue and skin tones. In both hands, they holds an oversized orange carrot. Background in a light blue.

Three individuals in yellow hazmat suits, equipped with protective gloves and masks. One person is seen planting a daisy, another is watering another daisy with a hose. The primary colors: yellow for the hazmat suits, the brown and red tones of the brick wall, white for the daisies, and various shades of green for the leaves.

A cracked egg with a bright orange yolk that's starting to drip. The egg white splatters in various directions. The background is a textured, dark gray surface.
Dominant colors: bright orange of the yolk, the white of the egg white, and the dark gray background.

A melting pumpkin against a stark, purple brick wall. The pumpkin is melting, with its contents dripping and flowing down, surrounded by green and orange flames. There's a prominent 'X' on one of its eyes. Dominant colors include the orange of the melting pumpkin, the bright green of the flames, and the deep purple of the brick wall.

Numerous intertwined lifebuoys, densely packed and overlap each other. They are colored predominantly in shades of red, white, and grey. In the bottom right corner, a hand with spread fingers emerges.

A young individual in a swimming cap and swimming trunks, holding onto a lifebuoy. The person is portrayed against a panoramic backdrop of a verdant landscape, showing fields, trees, and a sky. Predominant colors in this artwork include shades of green for the landscape, a mix of white and blue for the sky, and red and white for the person's outfit.

Four children with diverse cultural backgrounds, each wearing masks that bear symbols representing different religions and nations. The children are placed against a striped background of alternating colors. The signature of the artist is seen at the top right. A broad palette of colors is used, from the multicolored representations of the children to the contrasting stripes in the background. Each child's image is filled with a mixture of bright and bold colors. (On the artist's website is was explained that the work emphasizes that although we need to remain physically separated due to the pandemic, the shared challenges can bring us together spiritually and emotionally. It underscores the universal need for faith during times of social isolation and expresses a collective hope that scientists will discover a solution to the pandemic, which transcends geographical, ethnic, and religious boundaries).

A series of five portraits of notable figures. From left to right, the figures are Dalai Lama, Mother Teresa, Malala Yousafzai, Nelson Mandela, and Mahatma Gandhi. Each portrait is partially overlaid with geometric patterns in vibrant colors, which contrast with the more muted tones of the realistic portraits. (Note: in the artist's website, it is tated that the panel is a celebration of peace and the unity of peoples, celebrating a world without borders symbolized by characters who have won the Nobel Peace Prize).

A young child climbing a massive bookshelf filled with a multitude of colorful books. The child is reaching out for a book. The colors are varied, mostly blue, yellow, red, white. (On the artist's website, it's noted that the mural depicts a person climbing a bookshelf in a library searching for a book. This scene highlights the importance of books and Brazilian literature. The books portrayed in the mural were selected based on approximately 4,000 suggestions of favorite Brazilian titles that impacted childhoods. The top 150 recommended books are featured in the mural.)

A young person with long braids standing with their back to the viewer. They are holding a teddy bear in one hand, and the other hand is painting a large peace sign in the sky with white paint. The symbol is painted in white, contrasting against the bright blue sky. They are wearing a colorful, patchwork jacket and striped pants. their hair is styled in two long braids. The background is a bright blue sky with white, fluffy clouds, and there is some greenery at the bottom of the mural, representing grass. (On the artist's website, it's noted that the artwork aims to convey a crucial message: we must not lose hope of someday living in a world without wars, with humanity united in the pursuit of a better future for all.)

A singular human figure lying down, dressed in a textured gray suit. It could depict the figure of a homeless individual because of the worn-out appearance. The figure's features are accentuated by red blush spots on its cheeks and a red dot on the forehead. The individual is seen wearing round sunglasses, one hand supporting the head. A pair of black, lace-up shoes completes the attire. The background is red. There are a few real-world objects around, including two people for scale, a dilapidated wall segment, and some utility fixtures. Dominant colors: red and gray with touches of blue, black, and white.

Large whale figure composed of various urban and industrial elements, set against a two-toned background divided into deep blue at the bottom and a rain-drenched gray at the top. Dominant colors: blue and gray, with white, orange, and various shades.

Intertwined ropes or vines, each segment in different colors, against a bright yellow background. The design incorporates various elements like leaves, and a small, orange fish. The ropes or vines twist and turn. Various shades of green, blue, red, brown, and yellow. The background is a bright, solid yellow.

Two blue-hued humanoid figures enclosed within two separate circles adorned with leaf patterns. The figure on the left holds up a can with the label "Sugar" dripping off of it, while the figure on the right is about to drink from a can labeled "Killer Series". Dominant shades of blue for the humanoid figures and background, accented with white for the leaf patterns, text, and details on the cans.

Two side profiles of peoplewith natural landscapes incorporated into their silhouettes. Their hair and shoulders transform into green terrains with houses, trees, and even a small boat on a body of water. Dominant colors: hues of blue and pink. The peopleare depicted in colors with skin tones, while the landscapes are green.

A large polar bear seemingly diving or plunging forward. The bear, depicted in stark white and black (dark appearance of its lower half), giving the impression of being coated or drenched in oil. A turquoise circle sits behind the bear. Beige backdrop.

Blue whale is depicted within the confines of a larger, transparent whale-shaped structure made of ice. The iced whale is translucent, allowing viewers to see the blue whale inside. As the ice catches light. Dominant colors: shades of blue – from the deep blue of the whale to the lighter, more translucent hues of the iced exterior.

Two main characters: slice of watermelon with a smiling face and a dripping ear of corn. Both are using sombreros. The backdrop consists of shades of green that resemble the foliage or a garden. Some droplets and splatters can be observed. Dominant colors include green, red, yellow, and light blue for the background.

column4: Pray for peace in the barrios
column7: Main backdrop is a sky-blue brick wall. A white dove, symbolizing peace, flying above a banner that reads, "Pray for Peace in the Barrios." A yellow cross with a red rose in the center has the words "Que Viva La Raza" written underneath.The lower part of the mural showcases graffiti and street tags, some of which include the word "PEACE."
column9: The images are accessible for fair use. However, muralists retain all rights to their work, and Robin Dunitz retains copyright for the images. Any requests for permission to reproduce the images must be directed to: Robin Dunitz, 503-577-3842, rjdunitz@comcast.net

column7: The mural depicts a brown bear standing on its hind legs, with a large, vertically crumpled red fabric obscuring a portion of the bear's body. The background is plain natural, earthy tone.

Four distinct faces, each showing an expression of laughter. The faces appear to be from diverse age groups and possibly ethnicities. The color palette is mainly dominated by shades of blue, which contrasts with the splashes of pink colors around the faces.

Two figures in a seated position, close to each other. Their hands are intertwined. Background consists of a repetitive, ornate pattern in warm orange and yellow tones. There are paper airplanes scattered within the pattern. The figures wear clothing adorned with spots and stripes in various colors.

Two anthropomorphic bird-like figures stand side by side against a white brick wall. Above them is a banner inscribed with the word "Forever" and below that "Queer." One figure holds flowers in their hand, while the other wears a baseball cap with the letters "SF." Both figures have distinct tattoos; one has "Tweety" written on the arm and the other displays "So Hara." Dominant colors include white for the background, various shades of blue for the bird figures, and accent colors like green, pink, orange, and black for details.

A large black and orange bird perched atop giant, brightly colored oranges and a single lime. These fruits appear to overlap the structure of a green building, where windows, vents, and other architectural details emerge from the fruits. There are also large green leaves connected to the fruits. The dominant colors are green, orange, black, and hints of red.

Two side profiles of faces. On the left, a blue-toned face appears to be screaming or shouting, with hair or a form of energy flowing backward. On the right, there's a face, colored in shades of red, with an eye in focus and a tranquil expression. This red face seems to be dripping or melting, with lines resembling blood or paint running down the face. Dominant colors include shades of blue and red. There's also a touch of black, white, and orange in the details.

Workers against a backdrop of a red building with the word "LISNAVE." A person pouring liquid into a container, and a group of workers collaborating on a task. The Portuguese words "GENTE," (People), "MEMÓRIA" (Memory), "ARTE" (Art), "ALMA" (Soul), "ESPERANÇA" (hope) and "FUTURO" (Future) are integrated. Dominant colors are black, white, shades of gray and the red in the background.

A person, with their back turned, is depicted releasing a heart from a basket. Various flora and abstract designs. Other hearts and lips are scattered throughout the scene. A sign reads "seeds of REVOLUTION" in the lower center. Dominant colors are black for the designs, pops of red and pink for the hearts and lips, with a splash of yellow for one of the hearts. Background white.

A cartoonish blue creature with facial features. Beside the creature is a sign that reads "DON'T FEED THE CANCER", and below are multiple cigarette butts. Dominant colors: blue for the creature, white for the sign's background, and red for the lettering. The cigarette butts are painted in browns and tans. (Note: The artwork was created as part of the #do1cancer campaign to increase awareness and fundraise for the Colchester Hospitals Charity).

Close-up portrayal of a person's face, seemingly shouting. The facial features are detailed, with open mouth, sharp teeth, flared nostrils, and eyes. Color palette, primarily composed of skin tones, ranging from light to dark shades. The background is a muted gray.

An older person sitting in an intimate setting resembling a living space. Beside them, there's a wall showcasing various artwork, including paintings of figures. The room contains other elements like a plant, a table, a chair, and what appears to be an old-fashioned television. The person's clothing is adorned with intricate patterns. Color palette is relatively muted, with the dominant colors being browns, grays, and the whites and reds of the person's outfit. There are splashes of color on the wall and the green of the plant.

Hands cradling a detailed, picturesque landscape, complete with a body of water, mountains, a setting (or rising) sun, birds, and lush greenery. The artwork incorporates a real tree growing at the base of the building, making it appear as if the tree is an extension of the mural itself. The hands seem to be protecting the contained environment. The dominant colors include various shades of pink and skin tones for the hands. The landscape within the hands include blues for the water, deep greens for the vegetation, yellow for the sun, and muted browns and blues for the mountains.

Two young girls, one with dark skin and the other with light skin. Their faces merge in the center. Their hair is blue. The color palette contrasts warm earthy tones, representing the dark-skinned girl, with cooler pastel shades for the light-skinned girl. The point where the two profiles meet is a gradient blending the two color palettes.

A designed fish composed of various plastic waste items such as bottles, wrappers, and bags. This fish appears to be swimming upwards towards a cluster of bubbles. The primary colors are green, white, blue, and grey, with hints of brown.

To the right, a person is spraying or drawing using a can, a child-like representation of a rocket with a dog inside it. Above the rocket, there's a crescent moon and several stars. Predominant colors include white (for the building), blue (for the rocket), yellow (for the moon and stars), and red (for the girl's outfit).

Two primary figures – a slender, androgynous human form with their head turned to the side, and a large tiger, roaring amidst foliage. The human figure is depicted in grayscale with pronounced black outlines, while the tiger and foliage boast shades of red and purple. Predominant colors include grayscale for the human figure, and red, purple, and black for the tiger and foliage.

column4: A Mercearia (baseado numa foto de Artur Pastor)
column7: A storefront of a vendor's stall. An array of hanging foods or herbs in the store's entrance. Within the store's shade, a person is captured attending to goods, with a sign displaying prices next to them. Predominantly grayscale tones.

A collection of aquatic animals, predominantly whales, intertwined and layered. The animals seem to be trapped or encapsulated within a transparent cube filled with water. One whale at the bottom displays red stripes, which resemble tape or bindings. The predominant colors are varying shades of blue and gray representing the aquatic environment. There are splashes of red on the whale at the bottom.

A figure that appears skeletal with an elongated face and bright orange eye. It leans forward. The figure is draped in what seems to be a cloak or garment with black and red patterns. Above the figure, a bird holds a banner in its beak with a phrase in Portuguese: "NÃO HÁ MACHADO QUE CORTE A RAIZ AO PENSAMENTO" (translates to: "THERE IS NO AXE THAT CAN CUT THE ROOT OF THOUGHT"). Primary colors are blue, white, black, and red. The bright blue background contrasts with the figure's white face and red cloak.

An elderly person juxtaposed a dark blue backdrop featuring a silhouette of trees and a night sky. The person appears contemplative, with a detailed portrayal of their wrinkles, eyes, and headwear. Dominant colors: blues, white, and grayscale for the portrayal of the man.

A human eye, within which there's a detailed reflection of the Earth with a strong emphasis on the African continent. The eye is surrounded by a dynamic array of colors that intermingle in abstract patterns. Prominent hues of blue, yellow, red, purple, and green.

A side profile of a person with their eyes closed. They appears serene as they extends their hand towards a bird with a striking red crest, which is about to perch on their fingers. On the left, a large wing belonging to the woman. Surrounding the figures are leaves and smaller birds, all set against a pale sky backdrop. Dominant colors are soft blues of the sky, earthy tones in the person's skin and hair, whites and grays of the large wing, and the green leaves. A hint of red in the bird's crest.

A person (possibly a girl, although the face is not displayed) is sitting down with a book open in their lap. They hold a second book in their other hand. The person has long, dark hair, and is wearing a short-sleeved light green shirt and a maroon skirt. They are holding a book in one hand, and the book is open to a page. The background features a vibrant pink pattern with green plant-like shapes interspersed throughout. Several white sheets of paper seem to be floating in the air around them, suggesting breeze. In the foreground, there are several chairs and tables arranged as if in an outdoor café or garden setting. A circular window is set within the patterned wall, providing a glimpse into a dimly lit space. Dominant colors: earthy tones – browns, grays, and greens – with the red and white patterned wall.

A scene with two characters against a blue background. On the left, a person dressed in formal attire, wearing a white shirt, yellow tie, and dark pants. They are shown in a dynamic posture and expression, clenching their right fist and holding a piece of yellow paper in their left hand. A speech bubble above their head reads "PAR!!" maybe implying that they are shouting. On the right side, a bearded person with purple skin and yellow hair, sitting on the ground. They are dressed in a tattered yellow shirt and appears to be homeless, holding a tin can in their hands begging for money. The color palette is dark, with purples and blues being dominant.

A person sits on a container filled with beverage cans, with a fishing rod in one hand. On the adjacent cooler, a seagull is perched. Dominant colors: blue, elements of red, white, and gray. The cooler: red and white.
A mother and child resting together. A red bicycle is also integrated. The background is red in contrast with the monochromatic palette for the figures with shades of grey and white.

An infant (baby), closed eyes, with a backdrop of the Earth cradled by a pair of hands. The artwork has the phrase: "Everyday 400 babies are born with HIV", and is further emphasized with the phrases "#endAIDS" and "(RED)". Dominant colors include red, blue, turquoise, purple, orange, and skin-tones. The backdrop is a striking red, while the Earth and the baby feature a mix of the other mentioned colors.

Half-visible face in blue tones against a bright blue background. Adjacent to the face is a jellyfish with flowing tentacles that seem to interact with the face. Dominant colors are blue, black, white, and gold. The blue forms the majority of the background and the facial depiction, while the jellyfish carries uses gold with white and blue accents.

A young person holding a circular frame. Within the frame, there's a scenic depiction of white houses nestled amidst green hills under a blue sky with clouds. A large seagull is also depicted in flight, its wings extended, juxtaposed against the young person's figure. The color palette includes shades of brown, white, blue, green, and gray.

Two large figures - an adult person wearing a hat and a young person. Both are painted in vibrant colors. They are holding the Earth together. The background has an abstract geometric pattern. Colors: a spectrum of colors from the rainbow, with each figure predominantly featuring different shades. (Note: this mural was painted at the headquarters of the United Nations in New York, depicting a father handing the planet to their daughter).

A series of human figures, in colors of red, blue, and yellow, with a few figures in muted shades. The figures are interconnected, holding hands or raising their arms. The background has bands of color. At the top, the phrase "HANDS IN SOLIDARITY" can be seen. Dominant colors: red, blue, and yellow, with some figures in subdued tones.

column4: Hope: A message of hope on a mountain of skulls and on the wall of a destroyed house
column7: Artwork set against a backdrop of a dilapidated building, possibly war-torn or abandoned. On a fragment of wall, there's a mural of a person in a blue dress, reaching out to the word "Hope" painted above them. Beneath their feet is a layer of skulls, painted in blue with some inscriptions, including "DMC" and text in Arabic. Dominant colors: white and blue.

Three large grayscale facial expressions of a person (possiblt«y a woman), each showcasing different emotions. The backdrop is painted in deep blue with white streaks, resembling either rain or dripping paint. Colors: Predominantly grayscale (for the faces) and deep blue with white streaks.

An underwater scene where a child sits atop a gigantic whale, reading a book. The whale is surrounded by green birds in flight. In the corner, there's a signature or tag of the artist. Dominant colors: shades of blue for the water, gray for the whale, and greens for the birds. The child has a pink-striped shirt and a colorful backpack.

Side profiles of two individuals, a older person and a younger individual. The older person appears to be handing over a red apple to the youger person. The older person has a detailed hairstyle adorned with white beads, the younger individual is wearing a cap. Background with striped patterns in yellow and light blue, with detailed plants, flowers, and small yellow birds. The bottom section is a red with stylized blue leaves and symbols. There's the artist signature at the bottom right. Dominant colors: yellow, light blue, deep red, and green. Warm tones of the individuals' skin.

Monochromatic scene with the text "DRESS ME UP FOR BATTLE" at the top, followed by "WHEN ALL I WANT IS PEACE" and "THOSE OF US WHO PAY THE PRICE COME HOME WITH THE LEAST". Below the text is a group of individuals in a boat, rowing amidst stormy waters. One person in the boat holds up a flag with a splash of color, blue and gold. There's a signature os the artist at the bottom right.

A large, smiling face, seemingly of a young individual. Above the face, there is a hand holding a plant, which has bright green leaves and flowers. The word "EDUCATION" is inscribed on the wrist of the hand.Dominant colors include earthy tones such as browns and greens, with splashes of yellow, purple, and blue.

A sprawling mass of buildings, all tightly packed and leaning in various directions, as if they are on the verge of collapse. The structures are depicted in a muted, beige color. The buildings lack windows, doors, and other details that would make them functional, suggesting a dilapidated and abandoned state. In the foreground, a figure is standing on a solitary building. This figure is observing the chaotic mass of buildings. The figure is small in comparison to the overwhelming number of structures. The background features a pale blue sky. The ground on which the buildings rest appears barren and desolate. Dominant colors: beige, light brown, and light blue. (Based on the artist comments, it depicts men in cardboard kraft houses against a soft blue sky, inspired by the 2013 migrant influx to France. It reflects on the tough realities these individuals faced while seeking a better life that often remains out of reach. The artist uses this visual narrative to address this societal issue.)

column4: Education Is Your Shield and Trophy
column7: Shows a child enveloped in a blanket, cradled in its a person's arms. The person and child are rendered in a warm blue hue against a black background, resting above a bursting array of orange and yellow flowers with green leaves. Overlapping the images is the phrase: "The greatest education is your shield and trophy". Dominant colors: blue, red, orange, and green.

A shirtless person holding a yellow oar or paddle vertically. The person appears to be looking up with a shocked expression on their face, mouth open wide. They are wearing a swim cap. Above their head, there is a large hand in white and yellow, positioned directly on top of their head, as if it is pressing their down. The background is relatively plain. Dominant colors include pale blues, grays, whites, and yellow.

column4: Apenas o Coração Pode Bater ("Only the Heart Can Beat")
column7: A young person in a turquoise dress has a toy teddy bear with a blue ribbon near them. Above them, there are two hands manipulating puppet strings, suggesting that they are under someone's control. The background is a gradient of colors transitioning from dark to a vibrant red. Dominant colors include shades of red, turquoise, brown, and beige.

A person seemingly merging with a large cardboard box. The box has an outline of a human figure drawn on it, matching the man’s body. The person is holding the box close to their body with both arms, almost embracing it. their head is tilted to the side, resting on the top of the box. Only their feet are visible at the bottom, wearing red shoes that contrast with the muted tones of the cardboard and their skin. The background is blue.

A young person lying on their back, their legs bent at the knees, lying on the grass, with their shoes almost touching the sidewalk below. Above them, a wooden fence forms the background, with a scene of two young people with backpacks. Birds are painted both in the background and in the sky above. Dominant colors: shades of pink, green, blue, and brown.

A bird with a pencil-like pointed beak, soaring over an assortment of items such as a ruler, sharpener, cassette tape, pencil, and a book with the text "#Education Cannot Be a Crime". Colors of gray, brown, blue, red, green, gold, and pink. (Note: Created for the #NotACrime campaign. Based on the artistis comments, it features the Persian national bird, the nightingale, depicted taking flight with the aid of educational tools. Grey strings represent governmental control attempts to trap its wings, symbolizing the impediments to the right to education, reflecting the struggles of the bird and the people to ascend and thrive).

A person, wearing glasses and a pink shirt, holding a large stack of colorful books. Perched atop the books is a gray cat. In the backdrop, there are plant leaves and a floating cup spilling liquid, possibly tea or coffee. Colors: Pink, gray, brown, green, blue, yellow, and white.

An elderly person seated on the ground against a wall. They holds a cardboard sign with the written words "SAVE ME". Near them, but outside the paiting are other cardboard pieces. Colors: Brown, black, white, and the natural hue of cardboard.

Portrait of a young person looking down. A blue bird, possibly a macaw, is perched near their face, its beak almost touching their eye. On their t-shirt is a painted scene of a dock leading into a lake surrounded by green mountains. The background is yellow and has two windows. Dominant colors include the yellow of the wall, the deep blue and green of the bird, and natural colors on the t-shirt.

Three portraits of children against a colored background. From the left, the first child is adorned with face paint, beads, and a floral hair accessory. The second child has a curious expression and a blue backdrop, the third child is portrayed with their hand against their face, two bun hairstyles, and a bright yellow background. Colors: red, blue, and yellow in the background, complemented by the skin tones and attire of the children.

Two prominent figures surrounded by elements such as hands, butterflies, and flowers, wings. The top person figure seems to gaze upwards while the lower person one holds a heart and gazes to the side. Colors: purple, orange, and pink hues.

column4: Paz entre as Nações / Peace Among Nations /
column7: Collage of faces belonging to various ages and cultural backgrounds, segmented by colorful vertical stripes. Each face is detailed, capturing unique expressions and features, such as jewelry, facial tattoos, and headwear. A wide range of colors, notably green, blue, yellow, red, pink, and black, with vertical stripes.

Figure on the right appears to be in a position of either pulling or letting go of the hand of the figure on the left, who is draped in a striped cloth. The surrounding wall is adorned with three large paper airplanes, one of which appears to be directed towards an open real window. Dominant colors: beige, black, and white, with some muted browns in the background wall. (Note: A Wall Against Violence Towards Women)

column3: Aravani Art Project - Lead Artists: Chandri N, Purushi, Jyothi, Poornima Sukumar, Sadhna Prasad
column7: Multiple portraits of individuals, each framed by colored geometric and patterned backgrounds. The individuals appear to represent various ages, genders, and emotions. There is an real arched doorway in the center, surrounded by these portraits, through which vegetation can be seen. Colors: yellow, blue, red, pink, green, and orange.

Line-up of seven individuals. Each with distinct clothing and accessories, suggesting different professions or roles. From left to right: A construction worker wearing a yellow hard hat and an orange safety vest; A person in a green shirt holding a dark blue baby swaddled in a blanket; A person wearing a blue hijab and a white dress with red details, holding a baby bottle; A person in a blue outfit with a badge on their chest; A person with short, curly hair wearing a green shirt, holding a book; A person with dark hair in a bun, wearing a dark outfit and glasses, holding a notebook or folder; A person with glasses and a white coat, possibly representing a doctor or a scientist.The background is a solid blue; contrasted with yellow, red, and green in the clothing and accessories. (Note: A Gender Equity wall artwork emphasizing the importance of equal representation, opportunities, and support for all. The artist inverted traditional gender roles in their design: women are depicted as construction workers, chefs, business leaders, and scientists, while men are portrayed in roles typically seen as feminine, such as carers, nurses, and dancers. The idea is to empower women and inspire men by celebrating those in non-traditional roles, challenging societal norms and promoting gender equity).

A young person reaching upwards with their left hand, as if trying to grab something round above them. They are wearing a red and white striped shirt. The background is a mix of abstract, colorful shapes in shades of teal, blue, and green. The boy’s right arm appears to be resting.

Three individuals: a person holding a bag of fresh produce, a young person planting, and a person kneeling beside them. In the background, a landscape of fields with a windmill, set against a sky with clouds and an orange-hued sunset. Predominant colors: shades of orange, yellow, green, and blue, with elements of purple, red, and brown in the figures and details. (Note: The picture was created to highlight the issues of global food insecurity and food injustice affecting African-American communities).

A central portrait of a person with dark skin, their eyes closed in a serene expression, and their hair styled in braids adorned with beads. They wears a colorful necklace and a red garment with vibrant floral patterns. A white bird with outstretched wings, possibly an egret, is flying across their chest, emerging from their dress. Surrounding the central figure are two stylized side profiles of the person in blue hues, as if these images were cut in half with the person in the middle. Each adorned with patterns and decorations. These profiles appear almost like a reflection. The background itself is a mix of bright yellow, pink, and other colors, with abstract plant-like forms. Dominant colors: shades of pink, yellow, blue, purple, and teal; person's brown skin and white egret.

Close-up of a child's face looking through a window. The girl's right hand is pressed against the glass, fingers slightly spread, as they gazes outside with a thoughtful expression. The inside of the space on the left appears dark and cluttered with boxes, some with writings, and a teddy bear. Beyond the window, a scene depicts a bright, sunny day with a children's playground in the background. Colors: shades of brown, beige, and gray in the interior, with brighter blues and greens depicting the exterior playground scene.

Two children on a swing, suspended in front of a vividly colored, abstract background. The child on the left reaches upwards, perhaps trying to grasp the chains of the swing. Colors: turquoise, yellow, and orange.

A figure in a vulnerable position. Only the upper portion of the body is visible lying against a dark backdrop. The figure is depicted with pronounced tattoos on the arm, and appears to be holding an object. The clothing consists of a white tank top and purple garment. In the surrounding environment, there's a doorway and some litter on the ground, suggesting a neglected setting. The background is dominated by deep, dark hues.

A human figure, possibly a person, with an emphasis on the face and upper body. The individual is holding food in their hands. Small red dots are scattered around them. The artist's signature and a QR code are visible at the bottom corner. The palette consists of blues, greens, reds, and yellows.

A large book with a red cover and yellowed pages. Emerging from the book are two fish, appearing to swim out from between the pages. The book is placed on a green surface representing grass, with a small window at the bottom, blending the book with a building. The mural prominently uses red for the book cover, yellowish hues for the pages, green for the grass, and realistic colors for the fish.

A person lying on the street. their body is curled up on the edge of a sidewalk, and their head rests on their arm, which is bent beneath them. The person is dressed in a dark outfit, including pants and a shirt, which are covered in blue butterflies. The butterflies are scattered across their body, in contrast to the somber tones of their clothing and the gray background of the wall behind them. The wall is plain, with some faint writing or graffiti in the background. Dominant colors include shades of gray, black, and touches of blue from the butterflies.

Close-up view of several hands intertwined, some with lighter skin and the others with darker skin. Surrounding these hands are abstract, fluid patterns in shades of orange and yellow. Dominant colors include shades of orange, yellow, black, and the natural tones of the intertwined hands.

A large mechanical device, resembling a steampunk contraption, soaring above a cityscape. The device uses a brain as a hot air balloon to float, with pipes extending from it. A pair of hands holding an open book protrudes from the contraption, with the text "Imagine, Osez, Rêvez" (Imagine, Dare, Dream) visible on one of its pages. The backdrop consists of towering buildings, clouds, and a smoky ambiance, suggesting a city enveloped in fog or pollution. Dominant colors include shades of blue, gray, brown, and the soft pink of the brain.

A large, robot-like figure. This mechanized figure is depicted in a seated or crouched position, holding an open book in its hands. Its head is transparent and contains a human brain, which is presented on a stand or pedestal inside. Above the figure, a lightbulb illuminates the setting. The environment has an old-world ambiance with detailed brickwork, pipes, and vents. Dominant colors include shades of brown, gray, and the pink hue of the brain.

Two figures reaching out to each other, almost kissing, but separated by a segmented wall structure. Their bodies and faces showing a desire to connect despite the physical barrier between them. The backdrop is predominantly composed of various shades of blue. This artwork was painted on a piece of the Berlin Wall. Colors: mainly blues. The artist's signature is visible in the lower right corner of the mural.

A bee, crafted using various recycled materials, set against a green backdrop. The bee appears intricate with its wings spanning outward. Dominant hues of green and black, with highlights of yellow, gold, and brown. There are also traces of rust, suggesting the use of aged or weathered materials.

column4: Sesimbra é Peixe e Arte na Rua
column7: A lifelike portrayal of an older person with pronounced facial features, dressed in a checkered outfit. They appears against a watery backdrop with a boat and two figures in the background, one of whom is rowing the boat, while the other seems to be fishing. The primary palette consists of grayscale tones, with touches of blue in the water and the boat, and muted colors on the person's outfit.

Elderly person with a deep and thoughtful gaze, sitting in what seems like a contemplative pose. The person wears a dark cap, a greenish-blue jacket, and cream trousers. Elements such as air conditioners and pipes juxtapose against the figure. The backdrop features a unique blend of splatter-like patterns and muted colors, which contrasts the sharp details of the man. Dominated by muted tones of beige, greenish-blue, and gray. The splatter-like patterns in the background incorporate shades of gold, gray, and white.

A side profile of a person lying down with their chin resting on their hand. their gaze is directed forward. their right arm is extended downward, and it appears that an arrow has pierced their arm. Monochromatic color scheme, primarily using shades of purple and lavender. The "YOU KILLED ME FIRST," is tattooed on their arm.

An expansive structure of interconnected red and white floaters. A singular person appears to be enmeshed or emerging from this web of floaters. Dominant colors include the red and white of the floaters, beige background, and surrounding greenery.
A black person's face with a geometric background with red lines and black and white color blocks. The number "2700" is featured, corresponding to the postal code of the city.

The image depicts a person, who appears to be homeless, wearing a yellow coat and standing inside a trash bin. They are drinking from a mug from which steam is rising. The person has the lid of the trash bin on their head, topped with a banana peel. Visible inside the bin are a cup with a painted heart and various other types of indistinguishable trash. A green trash bag surrounds the bin. The dominant colors in the scene are yellow, orange, gray, and brown.

Three figures of a girl, captured in various dynamic poses, as if in motion, on a muted peach backdrop with windows. Dominant colors are peach (background), shades of blue (clothing), and natural skin tones.

A figure seated with their knees pulled close to their chest. T+G160heir long hair flows wildly in all directions, creating a sense of movement. The background is a vibrant and abstract swirl of colors, including reds, oranges, blues, and greens. Scattered throughout the background are geometric shapes, representing paper cranes or birds.
A young person lying down. their gaze is directed to the viewer. Dominant colors include blues, whites, oranges, and greens.

column4: Ciência e Fé / Science and Faith
column7: Close-up of a hand painted with the colors of the rainbow. Draped over the wrist is a stethoscope. The hand is set against a geometric backdrop consisting of triangles in various colors. The hand features the colors of the LGBTQ+ pride flag; the background is composed of triangles in shades of blue, green, yellow, orange, and red. (On the artist's website, it's noted that the mural was painted to honor São Paulo's 468th anniversary, located on the facade of the Hospital das Clínicas. This artwork, featuring a doctor's praying hands, underscores the harmony between faith in God and trust in medicine, expressing appreciation for the hospital's healthcare professionals.)

Two figures, an adult and a girl, embracing each other. The adult is dressed in a blue smock, while the person wears a white T-shirt. Both figures have their faces and hands painted in the vibrant colors. The person also carries a backpack in camouflage colors adorned with a peace symbol. They are set against the backdrop of a building resembling a school, indicated by a green chalkboard that features a drawing of wings. (This mural, created in Suzano, São Paulo, in response to the 2019 massacre at Raul Brasil school, was a community-involved initiative, drawing inspiration from the artist’s family members and creatively using pencil imagery in the peace symbol to promote remembrance and hope and a message of gratitude, expressing thanks to all educators).

column3: ETAM Boier Chylo Kome Pain Pener Roem Tone
column7: A green landscape populated by a towering tree, multiple treehouses interconnected by wooden bridges, and a large upside-down human figure at the bottom. Various elements of nature, including leaves and vine. Predominant colors are shades of green, representing the foliage, and earthy browns of the wood of the treehouses. The blue of the human figure's shirt and touches of red and yellow in the treehouses.

column4: The Braves of 9/11. Bravos do 11 de Setembro 2001
column7: A firefighter in full gear, kneeling against a backdrop of the American flag. The firefighter holds a hose, and there is a badge with the number "343" on the helmet. Colors: Red, white, blue, black, yellow in multiple shades. (Note: On the artist's website, it is stated that the mural seeks to convey sorrow for the many lives lost and to sympathize with those who lost their loved ones in the 9/11 attack—and subsequently, in the wars against terror triggered on that fateful day. It is also an honor to the courage of the men and women who worked in the rescue. The image is a reinterpretation of the photograph by Matthew Mcdermott, featuring Mike Bellatoni—one of the many heroes who survived that historic day. On the helmet, the number 343 is a reference to the number of firefighters who died that day; it also includes the Twin Towers and the flag of the United States. The stars may represent all the lives lost in the tragedy)

Four distinct human faces in colors, with each face divided into sections showcasing various hues and geometric patterns. Above these faces, the word "ELLIS" is written with similar geometric patterns in the backdrop. A broad spectrum of colors including but not limited to blue, yellow, red, green, purple, pink, and orange, with each face exhibiting a mix of these colors in segmented patterns. (On the artist's website, it is mentioned that the mural 'Ellis Island' features five faces representing different ethnicities. This symbolizes the diverse immigrant populations that have sought better lives in New York.)

Side profiles of Mother Teresa and Mahatma Gandhi. Mother Teresa, depicted with a white turban, with hands clasped. Mahatma Gandhi wearing glasses. The backdrop and figures are both adorned with a kaleidoscope of multi-colored geometric shapes. The architecture of the building, with stairs and balconies, is integrated into the artwork. (On the artist's website, it's noted that the mural features historical pacifist figures from India, emphasizing their dedication to peace and religion. The artwork illustrates that different religions should act as bridges, not barriers, reflecting a common goal of peace. This mural invites viewers to use dialogue as a tool for fostering a culture of peace.)

A person crouched inside a green trash bin. The person appears shirtless, has a dark cap and their posture is slightly hunched, with their head bent forward as if lost. They have a yellow paddle in their hands. The green trash bin stands against a beige wall, which has visible signs of peeling paint and old posters. The overall color scheme is muted. Dominant colors include shades of green (trash bin), tan, and brown (walls), and the natural skin tones of the figure.

Five portraits of diverse individuals, men and women, placed side by side with different cultural background. Above and below the portraits, abstract shapes and brush strokes in colors of yellow, blue, and red are present. The word "TOGETHER" stretches across the bottom, with the letters displayed in alternating colors of orange and teal.

A figure, seemingly crafted or pasted from brown paper, wearing a hood and positioned inside what appears to be a cardboard box. The figure has its head down. A red and white lifebuoy is visible on the cardboard box. The background consists of a wall with patches of red and white, along with some scribbled or painted marks.

This mural shows four people lying down and the hands on the stomach, one above the other, on different levels: The top person is wearing a crown and there’s a small symbol above the head. 2. The second person is wearing a hat. The third person is dressed like a police officer. The last person, at the bottom, is thin, nude, is lying on a life preserver and has a bag over the head, looking more fragile and painted in color skin. Most of the mural is in black and white, except for the red and white life preserver.

Large depiction of a human hand. The hand is painted with vibrant colors, with each region or segment of the fingers and palm showcasing different hues. The overlay of world continents is painted on the palm and fingers, suggesting a map of the world but in abstract and fragmented form. The backdrop of the artwork is a dark wall with windows.

Two children: a person with voluminous curly hair holding an open book on their lap, and a person beside them, playing with colorful building blocks that resemble LEGO pieces. The background has soft pink color, which contrasts with the vibrant colors of the children's attire and toys. (It was painted in a building known as "A Nossa Casinha," which serves as a hub for social, recreational, and educational activities).

column4: De la ausencia y de tí
column7: Three people in a shared activity. Each peopleis holding and inspecting a piece of fabric. The fabrics they hold are different shades of pink and white, and the peopleappear to be focused and contemplative in their actions. The background is a mix of darker tones with abstract shapes. Colors: shades of pink and white for the fabrics, with the peopledepicted in natural skin tones. The background consists of darker, muted colors of blue.

A human figure (man) with the body structure of a bird, perched on a wire with other four birds. The person is looking downward, possibly in the direction of the empty bench below. An olive tree branch hangs overhead, casting shadows on a warm beige wall. Colors: beige for the wall, natural green for the tree, and earthy tones for the figure and the birds.

A child turned away from the viewer, with their back facing outward. The child is wearing a pair of bright blue, polka-dotted butterfly wings. They are dressed in camouflage shorts and a brown shirt. The child is in a kneeling or crouching position, holding the stock and a portion of the barrel of a firearm. The background is a vivid red. The artist's name is written in the top left corner, and the signature "CPK" is located in the bottom right.

A young child, possibly a boy, wearing a cardboard box as if it were a helmet or space explorer's headgear. The child appears intrigued as they reaches out to touch a rocket toy in their left hand. The background ihas deep blue galaxy, complete with stars, a planet with rings, and other celestial sketches. The nebulous galaxy swirls into the shape of a pointing hand. A unique spaceship, an astronaut, and a crescent moon are also doodled on the blue backdrop. On the top right corner, the artist name can be seen.

The line-up of four iconic superhero faces (from left to right: Spider-person, Batperson, Captain America, and Iron Man) juxtaposed with the face of a medical professional wearing a surgical mask in the middle. A hashtag is written at the bottom: "#ZANASEHEROJE", which could possibly translate to a local language's expression of gratitude or appreciation for frontline workers. Additionally, there's a nameplate on the bottom right that reads "УЛИЦА ПОСПИТЕРА". A vibrant array of colors is used, mostly the trademark hues associated with each superhero.

column3: Adry Del Rocio & Carlos Alberto GH
column4: Nuestra fuerza colectiva no tiene fronteras
column7: Two females, possibly of indigenous descent, positioned adjacent to one another. The leftmost figure holds a nest with two birdlings while an eagle, with expanded wings seems ready to take flight from their hand. The rightmost figure merges into a cacti that transform into colorful butterfly wings as they extend rightward. A vivid palette with a spectrum of blues, purples, greens, and oranges.

Two peoplestanding side by side against a light-colored building. The person on the left has short, silver hair, wears a green sleeveless top, and holds an olive branch. The person on the right has an afro hairstyle, dons glasses, and is dressed in a white shirt and maroon skirt. They also holds an olive branch. Above them, there's an inscription on the building which reads, "Todos Somos Um" ("We are all One"). Colors muted with dominant shades of green, white, maroon, and the natural skin tones of the people.

Close-up depiction of a person's upper body and face in partial view. The chest is adorned with branches that have blooming red flowers. The petals of these flowers seem to be drifting away or being carried by an unseen wind. Colors: muted tones of pink, white, and grey, with red from the flowers.

Several individuals, possibly farmers, involved in the process of picking and collecting citrus fruits, likely oranges. These activities are painted on the walls of buildings. The predominant colors in the mural are earthy tones of brown, green, and orange. These shades reinforce the theme of nature, agriculture, and labor.

The mural depicts a large figure of a person with multiple arms. Each of their hands holds strings that are connected to their other hands. The person is with closed eyes and lips slightly parted. their hair is intricately styled in braids. They wears a detailed dress with a heart at the center of their chest. The background is plain brown. The mural employs a muted color palette, dominated by grayscale, brown with hints of red.

Portrait of a face with intricate geometric patterns, bright colors, and tribal-like adornments. The background radiates outwards in a sunburst pattern, and the Brazilian flag floats at the top. The piece employs a spectrum of colors, with each segment of the face showcasing different shades – blue, red, yellow, and green, among others. (On the artist's website, it's noted that it features a portrait of Chief Raoni, an indigenous leader from the Caiapó tribe. This artwork, part of a larger initiative to protect indigenous peoples and preserve the Amazon rainforest, aims to raise awareness of the challenges faced by indigenous communities globally. The mural emphasizes the importance of valuing ethnic diversity).

Three peoplestand side by side, hands interlocked. Their faces are not visible, as they are cropped from view. They wear long-sleeved shirts in distinct colors: green, blue, and maroon. The background is a neutral beige, which contrasts with the darker tones of their clothing.

A young person stands next to a wooden chair, positioned in front of a chalkboard with the repeated phrase "I will not say," written several times. They wears a school uniform consisting of a white blouse and a plaid skirt. Predominantly muted tones: green for the chalkboard, earthy browns for the chair and floor, and pastel hues for the walls, combined with the white and dark colors of the girl's uniform.

A person with long hair adorned with flowers stands with their back facing the viewer. They holds up a spindle, and a bluebird is perched on it. Two kites are flying in the sky behind them. Two potted plants are on a brick ledge in front of them. Soft pastel colors, light blue tones in the sky, green in the plants, and multicolored stripes on the girl's shirt.

A large, melancholic person with flowing black hair stands, bound by ropes, against a yellow background. Surrounding them are three melting or dripping buildings. Below them, on a platform with a water-like pattern, a person rows a boat amidst floating debris and miniature buildings. Colors: yellow background, contrasted by the cool blues of the girl's dress and the water pattern.
A monochromatic portrayal of a firefighter, depicted with a helmet with a shield emblem.

Pink and red color palette with a large hand positioned in a peace sign. The bold and evocative phrase, "Freedom, where are you?" is written next to the hand. Abstract shapes and strokes; an artist's signature or tag at the top left. Use of various tones, from the pale pink background to the deep reds of the central figures.

column3: Hygienic Dress League (HDL) Corporation, visual artists Steve and Dorota Coy
column4: THE EAGLE HAS LANDED PART II
column7: A figure with an eagle's head is dressed in a formal blue suit, holding a briefcase labeled "HDL Corp". The eagle's tie and handkerchief bear dollar signs. The dominant colors are blue, white, and gray, with touches of yellow and red, mainly on the eagle's beak and the dollar signs.

A person with golden hair and blue eyes with a cityscape background. The person wears a green top and has a flower adorning their hair. An expansive tree with white blossoms stretches across the blue sky, partially overshadowing the gray buildings of the city.

A small, dark-colored, and precarious boat, with several human figures depicted in white, appears to be floating. The figures are huddled together, seemingly trying to escape or survive the dangerous situation below, where several figures are falling into a red sea. Below the boat, sharp, jagged shapes outlined in yellow and black resemble large open mouths or something devouring the falling figures. The background features a blue sky. The dominant colors are blue, red, black, yellow, and white.

A bird, with its wings spread wide, dominates the image. The bird's feathers are painted in many colors. Part of the bird is shadowed. The bird is looking to the left. Below the bird, the phrase "PAZ NO MUNDO" (translated as "Peace in the World") is written in Portuguese. The background consists of three colors: a pale yellow on the left, a light blue on the right, and an orange band at the bottom. Additionally, the building's façade features four small, square, real windows that are integrated into the mural. Dominant colors include: blue, pink, yellow, green, orange, white, and black and the multiple of shades creates a rainbow effect.

At the top, two depictions of children in profile wearing helmets and military attire and carrying backpacks, one facing forward and the other raising a hand in a salute or wave. Their figures are outlined against a blue background with a swirl pattern. Below the children, there is a large, stylized face. The person's eyes are closed, and their head is adorned with a colorful headscarf, surrounded by elements like a floating heart, a flying saucer, and a disco ball-like hand. The headscarf and the surrounding elements are multicolored. Around their head, abstract elements—like cubes and patterns intertwine. In the lower part, a small human figure, possibly a child, stands at what looks like a doorway or window that is integrated into the side of the person's face. This figure seems to be stepping into or out of a different dimension. Dominant colors: blue, pink, yellow, green, and red.

A child reaching upward with both arms extended toward the sky. The child’s left arm is wrapped in a blue ribbon and the right arm in a red ribbon, both twisting around the arms. The child looks up with a smile. Above, there is a treehouse set on a tall, twisting trunk, with a wooden door and windows. A pink pig with wings flies out from the balcony, and a large yellow butterfly appears nearby. The background features a bright blue sky filled with white clouds and a colourful kite. Below the treehouse, a green landscape includes a winding path, a small wooden fence, flowers, and a few scattered objects such as a wooden barrel. The main colours are blue, green, brown, and the bright tones of the ribbons, butterfly, and kite.

The silhouette of a child in black and white, shown from behind while drawing or writing on a wall. The child’s sketches include simple, childlike motifs such as a smiling sun, clouds, and a house, rendered in thin black outlines against a plain background. The composition uses a minimal colour palette of black, white, and beige tones.
column8: Patrícia Arriaga (can also be seen at https://www.instagram.com/p/CksvB5EKnWB/)

column4: Tenho em mim todos os sonhos do mundo
column7: At the forefront, a figure of a person wearing a flowing dress and she's depicted in a grayscale tone. This person is riding a vibrantly patterned zebra that is painted in black and white. The background is a mosaic of colorful squares and rectangles, juxtaposed with green foliage and trees. The backdrop is filled with a rainbow of shades, while the trees add various greens to the scene. The person and the zebra are in monochromatic tones.
column8: Patrícia Arriaga (can also be found at https://streetartnyc.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/ozearv-street-art-portugal.jpg)

column7: Abstract representation of a human figure, depicted with an elongated neck. The face is depicted as a hollow space, with concentric lines outlining the head. Inside the hollow area where the face should be, a house is visible, with its structure detailed. The house appears to be floating. The figure's hands, painted in blue, are positioned in the foreground, clasped together. The hands are oversized compared to the rest of the body and are adorned with a few simple line details. The background of the mural is predominantly pink, and there's a signature "MAR" on the top corner. The dominant colors are pink, with golden yellow on the neck and cool blue on the hand. The house inside the head has earthier tones.

A young child holding up a small plant with glee. Above the child, there's a face inside the sun with beams emanating from it. Surrounding the child are various elements, including cacti, geometric shapes, and other abstract forms. The word "TAMAULIPAS" is seen at the top. The mural has many colors, ranging from bright pinks, blues, and yellows to soft purples and greens.

A series of face outlines, each rendered in a single, bold color, layered atop one another against a background of horizontal stripes. The individual faces display a variety of expressions. At the bottom, the text reads "QUEEROES" followed by "CON MUCHO AMOR" (Translation: "with much love") and then mentions two artists. The mural embraces a rainbow of colors, reminiscent of the LGBTQ+ flag.

A scene shows a person's arms and hands, wearing a printed blouse, kneading or grinding something on a table. The table at which they works displays a ceramic vase, a cup, and a vase full of dried flowers. In the foreground is a wooden tool with a carved end (traditional kitchen utensil). The colors are earthy, from the browns of the arms, utensils, and scenery to the soft greens, blues, and reds of the clothes and ceramic objects.

column3: ALE POIRÉ + Janín + Mari Mariel + YUDA
column7: Juxtaposition of three scenes. On the left, four individuals in hats and light-colored shirts, working in a field with tools. Their backs face the viewer, and ropes tie them together. Below, at the bottom left corner, a pair of hands is depicted, reaching out towards a single plant. On the right, a figure (likely a woman) is enveloped in a shawl or cloak of intertwined plants and vines. This individual appears to be embracing or protecting the vegetation. Dominant colors: Dark and earthy tones, such as browns, greens, and purples.

Two figures are depicted in a stance as if they were holding firearms, but instead of guns, they wield flowers, specifically large white lilies. The painting is created on the surface of what appears to be a football (soccer) field, with the lines of the field visibly framing the scene. The background is composed of soft blues and purples. Dominant colors: blue, purple, white, and green.

Two people against a bright pink background. On the left, a person with face a face painted brown and some reflection in yellow has long d+G139ark hair. They holds a skull in their hands. A lit candle is placed beside them. On the right, another person with a face painted in rose, has long dark hair, is wearing a straw hat and smiles softly while holding a large bouquet of marigold flowers. Another lit candle is positioned near the second person, further emphasizing the theme of remembrance. The background is decorated with a rose lace-like pattern, and in the center, between the two women, are the words "CONTIGO EN MEMORIA" (which translates to "WITH YOU IN MEMORY"). The dominant colors are pink, orange, white, and shades of dark brown.

Two hands holding each other. One hand is depicted in a realistic style with natural skin tones, while the other hand is depicted in a black and white sketch style. The background is minimalistic, with soft grey tones surrounding the hands.

Two people sharing an intimate moment, with their faces close to each other, set against a weathered brick wall. A visible rail is positioned in front of the artwork, and the artist's signature is displayed in the top right corner. Mainly natural skin tones, green, brown, beige, and the diverse hues of the bricks which range from yellows to pale greens.

A scene between an adult, likely a healthcare worker wearing a mask, and a young child. The child, also in a mask, is extending a flower towards the adult, who appears to be in a moment of contemplation or exhaustion. The predominant colors are soft shades of blue, beige, and the pastel hues of the background tiles.

A central figure appears to be emerging from a shadowy, abstract background. The figure is predominantly dark, with features that include antlers extending from the head, giving it a mythical appearance. The figure’s face and upper body are highlighted in a bluish hue, contrasting with the darker tones of the rest of the body. They are holding a small figure of a bird in their right hand. The bird is also depicted in dark tones with some highlighted areas that give it a spectral quality. The background is a mix of blues, purples, and pinks. The text with the artist's name is in the bottom right corner. The dominant hues in the artwork include turquoise, dark blue, pink, and black.

Three children, each distinctively colored, gathered around a single individual who is holding a book. Their attention is directed towards the book. The scene is set against a backdrop of abstract shapes, symbols, and patterns. The color palette is diverse, including shades of blue, yellow, purple, white, black, red.

A central figure of a person's face in a monochromatic tone, with shades of grey and black. The background around the person is filled with various geometric patterns and symbols. To the left of the woman’s face, diagonal stripes in blue and black run across the wall. Within these stripes, black floral patterns are visible. There are also pink and turquoise abstract shapes scattered throughout the mural. On both sides of the mural, there are prominent gender symbols, which are painted in a combination of black. 
The background has a mix of colors including blue, pink, yellow, and turquoise, blending together in a gradient-like effect. There are also two real windows on the wall, incorporated into the mural, which are partially obscured by the artwork.

column4: A house is not a home
column7: An overloaded cart being pushed and pulled by four individuals, two adults and two children. The cart is filled to the brim with a chaotic assortment of items, including several houses, a large number of furniture pieces, and various household objects.The background is filled with a dense black pattern, which contrasts with the bright colors of the items in the cart. Four figures are engaged with the cart: two seem to be pushing or guiding it from the back, while the other two appear to be pulling or leading it from the front using ropes. These people seem to be working hard to move the cart. (Note: Represents a saturated urban landscape with influences from pop art, folk art, and informalism, reflecting on habitable space and its various realities).

A close-up of a northern white rhino's face, with its horn visibly cut off, against a backdrop of yellow and teal colors. On the mural, a date is inscribed: "18.03.2018", accompanied by the text "Sudan, world's last male northern white rhino dies". Below this is a haunting message, "WHO IS NEXT...".
