Below there is an additional artwork of a town scene on the lower teal portion. In the surroundings, there are urban elements like two windows, and a streetlamp. Dominant colors include yellow and teal. The rhino itself is depicted in monochrome.

A polar bear that appears to be swimming against a backdrop of blue of fragmented ice. The bear is positioned near a real window, integrating the existing real structure into the artwork. Dominant shades of blue and white for the background, representing water and ice and the white polar bear. There are also smaller portions of grays.

An optical illusion of a three-dimensional pit or space in the ground. On the edge of this space stands a young person dressed in blue with a red cap. They appears to be trapped in an underground area with small windows. The person is holding a vase and has their head tilted downward. The surrounding area consists of a cobblestone path and the facade of an aged building with red wooden doors - the interior of a prison. Dominant colors in this piece include shades of blue, red, grey, and beige. The surrounding architecture incorporates browns and muted reds. (Note: An anamorphic artwork for the MX ARTS TOUR at Château du Taureau, France. It centers on the Château's role under the Ancien Régime, where Breton aristocrats were imprisoned by their own families to avoid scandal, with offenses ranging from libertinism to gambling. Although modern society has grown more accepting of individual differences, the work comments on the ongoing lack of complete acceptance).

An assortment of toy cars tightly packed together in various orientations. These cars, reminiscent of collectible toy models, are portrayed in a vertical cascade. Dominant Colors: red, green, blue, orange, yellow, and more.

column4: Customs and Traditions Mural (for the Vilaflor Chasna Tenerife City Council)
column7: Rural and agricultural scene. On the left side, there is a white donkey harnessed to a plow or a similar farming tool. Next to the donkey, various flowers and plants. In the center, a person dressed in a black shawl and a wide-brimmed straw hat sits on a small wooden chair. Behind them, a picturesque landscape with a large, terraced mountain and an arched bridge. To the right, hands holding pruning shears in an act of gardening. Below these hands, a small bird is perched on a branch. Several colors, including browns, grays, greens, blues, and subtle pinks.

Three figures painted in colorful tones against a background of intersecting geometric shapes and gradients. The left figure is a person with their eyes closed or looking down. their arm is painted with a mix of colors, and their fist is clenched. The central figure, a younger person, looks directly at the viewer. It appears that they have something in their mouth. They seems connected to the first man. The right figure is a person with glasses, smiling and making a peace sign with their fingers. Below these figures, there are two real rectangular windows incorporated. The background is filled with bright, dynamic colors such as purple, blue, orange, and green..

column4: Homenaje a las Mujeres Rurales de Barlovento La Palma
column7: Two elderly persons with detailed facial expressions. On the left, a person is depicted with a smile, their eyes closed, holding a piece of fabric in their hands, possibly knitting or some craftwork. Their shirt depicts a landscape with a sunset over rolling hills. There is an extra hand-painted green on the left, which appears to be holding the green landscape of the mountain depicted on the person's shirt. The person on the right wears a blue jacket and a grey knitted hat. They have a stern expression, and they lean on a stick. Next to them, two goats appear, one resting against their side, whereas the other goat is depicted between the two people and appears to be looking towards the viewer. The mural incorporates the building's windows, with some of the windows overlapping the figures. The colors are predominantly earthy tones, with greens, blues, and browns dominating.

Two portraits of men, with one wearing glasses, and the other older with a beard. Both faces are superimposed on a backdrop filled with graffiti with various symbols, doodles, writings, and other illustrations. A broad spectrum of colors, ranging from the more muted tones of the portraits to the vivid yellows, reds, blues, pinks, and many others in the graffiti.

An elderly person on the left and an elderly person on the right. Both are portrayed in farming attire surrounded by elements of agriculture and nature. The person holds a pitchfork, and the person carries a spade on their shoulder while presenting a handful of grapes. Their clothing merges with nature, taking on the appearance of terrains, vines, fruits, and flowing waters.A diverse range of colors is used, from vibrant yellows that dominate the background to the earthy greens, blues, and browns that detail the figures and their environment. (Note: Tribute to two key agricultural practices in the municipality of Los Realejos: the cultivation of the potato and the braided vine. It honors two "Titans of Agriculture," Doña Amparo González from Cruz Santa and Don Vicente Suárez from Icod el Alto, who have dedicated their lives to farming, nourishing past, present, and future generations).

Depiction of viticulture and winemaking. On the left, a person with green hair is shown holding a glass of wine that reflects a landscape with a castle or mountain in the background. In the center, large hands are holding clusters of grapes. To the right, an older person is pouring grapes from a basket. The dominant colors in the mural are green, purple, orange, and red. The mural is integrated with the surrounding environment with windows of the building used as part of the composition.

A cherubic child with bright red hair and blue wings. The child is holding a gold-colored gun in each hand, from which heart-shaped bullets are being fired. The bullets are accompanied by puffs of smoke. The child wears a string of bullets around its torso and has a tattoo of a butterfly on the right leg. Dominant shades of purple and pink in the background. The child is predominantly in hues of red (hair), blue (wings), and soft beige (skin). (Note: A message against war, emphasizing the urgent need for peace with the bold statement "WAR MUST STOP!")
column9: With the last photo you need to ask the organiser of the mural PIK in Białystok pik@pikpodlaskie.pl.

column7: An elderly person sitting on a bench that appears to be submerged in water. They are holding a cane and has a bird perched next to their on the bench. The scene includes elements like a mailbox on the left, a bottle floating in the water, and a tree trunk with branches on the right. A vivid color palette with dominant shades of purple, red, orange, and green.

A person, wearing a breathing helmet. The helmet encapsulates their head, with tubes connected to it. They holds a transparent bottle containing greenish plants or organisms. The background is a deep blue, contrasting backdrop to the green emanating from the helmet and bottle.
A monochrome person sheltering himself under a newspaper, with a briefcase by their side. The brick wall serves as a backdrop for the person, while next to their stands a real turquoise public phone.

Two weathered refrigerators, both slightly ajar. Emerging from the refrigerator on the left is a person who appears to be cautiously peeking out, their body halfway through the door. The refrigerator on the right is tilted, with another individual huddled inside it, appearing cramped. This person is curled up in a fetal position. The entire scene has monochromatic tones.

Two individuals. One, appearing to be in business attire, is leaning down, extending a piece of paper towards the other, who appears to be a homeless person sitting on the ground. Monochromatic shades of gray, black, and white.

A group of figures lined up in a row inside a cabinet or closet. The cabinet has one door open, from which one of the people is stepping out, moving forward with their head slightly bowed. The rest of the figures are inside, visible through the open door, standing upright and closely packed together. The closed door on the right side of the cabinet hides part of the figures. All the figures are dressed identically in white shirts, black pants, and red ties.

A figure, seated and bent over, holding out a wine bottle from a self. The shelf has multiple wine bottles lined up, with one bottle seemingly falling off the shelf on the right. The color palette is primarily monochromatic in shades of gray, black, and white.

A young person reading a book. Behind their is a pile of books labeled with various subjects like "ART," "HISTORY," "LAWS," "SCIENCE," and more. Above this pile, there is a robotic figure in a space-like environment, and beneath the books are elements like a plant, a sunflower, and an architectural structure. The mural uses a vibrant range of colors, from the rainbow spectrum behind the reader to the varied hues in the space scene and the books.

Five children, likely students, wearing school uniforms. Four of them are walking to the left while wearing face masks, and each carries a unique backpack. The fifth individual is on the right, also donning a face mask, and holds a placard with the message: "STOP RUNNING I AM NOT THE VIRUS." Dominant Colors: Yellow and browns for the uniforms with some red elements, and blues in the background.

A vivid mural of multiple hands of varying colors and shades encircling and embracing a representation of planet Earth. The background consists of a tapestry of vibrant abstract shapes and colors. Dominant colors: hues of yellow, red, green, blue, and purple, among others.

Three children smiling standing side by side, each with their arms resting on the shoulders of the others. The child on the left is wearing a green shirt with a globe and the word "Stand" on it. The middle child is dressed in a red shirt with a white peace sign symbol. The child on the right is wearing a blue shirt with the word "Tolerance" and a heart symbol, and their hand is giving a thumbs-up. The background is colorful, with dominant hues of green, blue, red, and yellow.

Colorful depiction of hands forming the word "LOVE". Each letter is represented by a hand gesture, with patterns filling the shapes of the hands. Above the hands forming the letters "L" and "O", a red and white banner with the phrase "WE ARE IN THIS TOGETHER" in red is displayed. The background is composed of several colors.

Various figures, primarily young African individuals, holding books or donning graduation caps. There's a young person with an illuminated outline holding a bouquet of flowers juxtaposed against another figure in a graduation cap. The backdrop includes the African continent and some books. On the right, a powerful message reads: "PAY MY SCHOOL FEES NOT BRIDE PRICE." The palette predominantly features deep blues, bright yellows, reds, and natural skin tones.

column4: It takes a natural disaster to reveal a social disaster.. Accra will rise again -Accra flood 2015
column7: A young child emerging from the water. Behind them, a city appears to be flooded with several people stranded amidst the deluge. Buses, cars, and buildings are partially submerged. There's a fire in the background with plumes of black smoke rising into the sky. A quote in the background reads, "Sometimes it takes a natural disaster to reveal a social disaster". Colors: Muted tones of brown, grey, and blue dominate the scene.

column4: P O S S I B L E
column7: A person in profile, their eyes closed. Their headwrap seamlessly transitions into a landscape featuring various animals, including a kangaroo with its joey, and a koala. Large green leaves with berries are depicted below, while a soft sun sets in the background next to the person's face. A real bicycle is positioned against the wall beneath the painting. Colors: Earthy tones such as browns and greens, complemented by shades of blue and orange. (Note: The theme "POSSIBLE," emphasizing the interconnectedness of humanity and nature, highlighting that they are inseparable in addressing the climate crisis.)

A large bird, possibly a kookaburra, depicted in detail on a blue-tiled wall. Below this bird, on a branch, sits a smaller bird with yellow and black patterns. Toward the bottom, a reptile is seen, possibly a lizard or gecko. The backdrop consists of swirling shades of blue, intertwined with branches and leaves. The words "Reduce, Reuse, Recycle" are inscribed in cursive, with the artist names at the top-left corner. Colors: shades of blue serve as the background, earthy tones in the birds and reptile, and pops of yellow in the smaller bird.

An individual (apparently a boy), draped in a patterned blanket, reading a book. Surrounding the person are elements of a room, including a wooden cabinet, an open window, and a door. The room is filled with floating papers, plants, and a bird with spread wings. Various other birds, including an owl, are depicted either perched or in flight. The room appears to transform into a natural setting with plants, as beams of light pierce through. Colors: Warm and rich hues, with tones of red, brown, and gold. The room's brick background and wooden elements provide a rustic feel, while the birds and plants introduce splashes of yellow and green. (Note: The mural is located on the town's central library, depicts a person reading under the covers, their imagination bringing the book to life. The scene is filled with local flora and fauna, including the endangered Regent Honey Eater, blending the joy of reading with an emphasis on regional wildlife conservation).

A cross-section of soil, revealing both its surface and what lies beneath. Above ground, there's a bounty of fresh produce, including fruits like strawberries, orange slices, watermelon, and grapes. Below the surface, we see the roots of these plants and vegetables like carrots and beets, intertwined with other subterranean elements. Colors:
The fruits and vegetables display reds, oranges, purples, and greens, while the background is blue.

A person is sketching or painting a scene on a long canvas. their depiction includes a picturesque landscape with serene waters and avian life, namely a couple of large birds. Surrounding their are hues and scattered art material. The artwork utilizes a broad spectrum of colors, from the cool blues of the water and sky to the warm oranges and reds of the tree foliage. The person is predominantly cool-toned. (Note: "Day Dreamer" reflects on the dream of homeownership and comfortable living. Prompts viewers to consider how desires for housing development might impact local environments).

A bold pink background featuring a series of abstract, geometric shapes and objects depicted in a minimalist style with white and black outlines. On the left side of the mural, there is a large rectangular box resembling a to-do list, with the text "To Do: 10. Fight Inequality" written inside. Below this text, a colorful circular symbol. The mural includes various objects such as what appears to be a pencil, a lightbulb, and other abstract shapes arranged in a dynamic composition. The hashtag "#WorldsToDoList" is present. The background colors are predominantly pink and white with elements of black outlining the shapes. (Note: Collaboration with the UN Global Partner, Project Everyone, and the global goals, the piece is part of the 'World’s To-Do List' campaign, aimed at reducing economic inequality. It powerfully illustrates the growing wealth disparity, showing the disproportionate impact on low-income families while the wealthy accumulate ever-greater wealth).

A person cycling past a vibrant landscape with green hills, blue skies, and stylized representations of buildings. In the background, there's a depiction of a mountainous range under a clouded sky, and in the foreground, there is a whimsical character alongside the cyclist. On the right, there is an ornate clock structure showing two different times. The dominant colors are blue, green, white, and red, with touches of beige and black. (Note: Involved collaborating with local teacher Robbie Keast to develop workshop series that aligned with The global goals, supported by Unesco and the North Devon Biosphere. Engaged over 200 children from six primary schools, emphasizing the region's unique ecology and its status as the first UK UNESCO World Heritage site to achieve Biosphere recognition).

column4: CONSUMERISM CONSUMES US - Il consumismo ci consuma
column7: A giant cigarette horizontally across the entire wall. The cigarette is illustrated in a deconstructed style, with the ash and burnt section on the left made up of various mechanical parts, metal pieces, and debris, giving it a chaotic, industrial feel. The middle part of the cigarette, where the paper and tobacco are usually present, is shown in shades of white and light gray, filled with detailed, swirling patterns that give a sense of disintegration. The right side of the cigarette, representing the unlit tobacco, is depicted in bright orange tones, with intricate details that resemble both flames and organic patterns.

A large towering robot with blue legs, standing amidst a chaotic landscape littered with various objects, including bottles, containers, and other debris. The robot is equipped with a pair of large mechanical pincers instead of hands, one of which is reaching towards the ground. A smaller figure, possibly a child, is depicted reaching up towards the robot, seemingly interacting with its head or control panel. The child is dressed in orange and brown clothing, contrasting against themechanical and industrial scene. The background is painted in a gradient of yellow, transitioning from a lighter hue at the top to a deeper, more intense yellow towards the bottom. Scattered throughout the mural are floating objects, such as bottles and containers, adding to the sense of disarray. The lower part is filled with debris, with some elements appearing to be parts of broken machines or discarded technology. The heap at the base consists of grays, whites, and blacks with occasional blue touches.

On the left, a large monochromatic bird is depicted with a can tied to its leg, releasing a colorful spray. In the center, the recycling symbol is constructed with green plant-like designs. To the right, there's a concentric circle resembling an "on" button surrounded by yellow and orange rays. Monochromatic shades (bird), green, yellow, orange, and red.

A small figure, a person with a cartoonish, stylized appearance, struggling to carry a massive, chaotic structure on the back. This structure is an intricate mix of mechanical parts, gadgets, and abstract forms. The structure includes various elements like gears, pipes, wires, and even what seems to be a robotic or mechanical face. On the right side, there appears to be a bird-like head integrated into the chaotic structure being carried by the figure. The head has a beak, wide eyes, and is depicted in a cartoonish style, blending with the mechanical elements of the structure. The background is a solid, bright magenta color that contrasts sharply with the detailed, darker tones of the structure being carried. To the left side of the mural, there's a real red emergency fire box mounted on the wall.

A densely packed sea of mechanical fish against a teal backdrop. Emerging from the sea is a hill or mound, atop which a city or castle stands. A single mechanical bird or periscope surveys the landscape from the left side. Colors Teal, blue, gray, brown, and a touch of pale red and yellow.

A split landscape highlighted by two different suns—an orange sun on the left and a white one on the right. Each side portrays forested terrains. At the center, there's a green recycling symbol formed by herbal leaves. Predominantly green with shades of orange, white, and teal.

An intricately detailed orange structure resembling a hybrid between a city and a creature with pointed ears, whiskers, and feline-like eyes. This "city-creature" emits dark smoke from its stacks, extending tentacle-like limbs, with one of its ends gripping a dense cluster of grey buildings. The background is painted in a deep shade of blue.

A large bird with an emphasized eye, appearing to look towards a series of industrial buildings emitting yellow and red emissions. The industrial structures seem to include towers, smokestacks, and other equipment typically associated with factories. Predominant colors include blues in the background, representing the sky or atmosphere, as well as blacks and grays for the factories. The bird is painted in shades of blue, white, and green with a red for its eye. Yellow and red lines flow from the factories. (Note: "A factory and a bird" metaphorically depicts artists as migratory birds, seeking refuge from industrial cities to rejuvenate their creativity. It features a scene of a factory set with a small bird observing from afar).

A large turtle whose shell is made up of various electronic devices such as mobile phones, keyboards, and computer chips. A streak of yellow, possibly representing emission, runs through the scene. The dominant colors are grayscale tones for the electronic devices, with white for the turtle's body and yellow for the flowing emission.

Several juxtaposed scenes across its breadth. On the left, there's a deer's head against a blue backdrop. The center displays a small urban or village scene with a human figure, houses, and emissions from chimneys. On the right, a surreal creature combining an eye, a beak, and flamingo legs stands against a burgundy background adorned with flying insects. Dominant colors include burgundy, blue, and white.

In the upper part a large, dark airplane propeller blade pointing upward. The propeller blade is painted in black. Behind it, the sky transitions from deep blue at the top to a lighter blue. The sky is filled with factory smoke. There are also bees flying around in the sky. In the middle section, the propeller blade cuts through what appears to be an elephant carrying a variety of objects on its back, (a car, a bicycle, and above, a cityscape with factory buildings emitting smoke with a ed-and-white striped construction cone), all stacked on the animal's back. The elephant’s feet are positioned on a broken cigarette, which is also emitting smoke. The elephant is looking downward, and it appears unsteady as it balances on the broken cigarette. The precarious positioning suggests that the animal is struggling to maintain balance. In the lower section of the mural the propeller blade extends, and we also see bees in this area flying around the blade. The bees are painted with yellow and black stripes. The background in the lower part is a light green or teal color, with curved white and blue lines that could represent movement or some abstract form of energy. Overall, the mural uses a palette dominated by dark tones (blacks, grays), industrial colors (metallic shades), and contrasting bright elements (red and white from the construction cone, yellow and black from the bees). The sky has blue tones, and green in the lower part. (Note: An artwork about Environmental sustainability).

On the left, there's a large light bulb containing a tree with blooming flowers, surrounded by industrial and urban depictions. On the right, an outer space scene is depicted with a planet, stars, and a floating astronaut. A staircase bisects the artwork. Colors: Blue, white, yellow, green, brown, and black.

A large, circular and mechanical structure and buildings is floating in the air with black smoke emitted from it. Below, a human figure rides a bicycle while holding a bycicle and interacting with a vibrant pink bird. Splashes of colors and patterns fill the surrounding area. Turquoise, green, pink, black, white, and yellow.

column4: Le Naufrage de Bienvenu/The Shipwreck of Bienvenu
column7: A gigantic figure sitting with the knees drawn up to their chest, positioned on the side of a large dam structure. The figure, wearing a gray hoodie and an orange safety vest, seems to have a fatigued posture, with its head resting on the legs. The figure appears to have three arms, suggesting movement. One of the arms is holding a small green piece of paper that features a landscape scene. The color palette of the mural is primarily muted, with shades of gray for the figure's clothing and the structure of the dam, contrasted by the bright orange of the safety vest and the green of the paper. The snowy landscape surrounding the dam is white.

An individual lying on the ground with their face completely obscured by a bucket covering their head. The person is wearing only socks, shoes, and underwear, with the rest of their body unclothed. The individual is positioned in a fetal-like pose, with one arm stretched out and the other bent, as if supporting themselves. The bucket is dark in color, contrasting with the lighter tones of the person's skin and clothing. The ground appears to be rough and worn, with earthy and muted colors.

A person seated on the ground with a slouched posture. The figure is depicted with a tired or contemplative expression, resting their head on their hand. They are wearing a white helmet and a red vest over gray clothing. The person is sitting with their knees drawn up, and their legs are crossed at the ankles. Their shoes are gray, and there are red accents on the socks. The background includes what appears to be an industrial or workshop setting, with an unfinished, rough texture to the walls. The artwork seems to integrate into its surroundings, creating the illusion that the figure is part of the physical space rather than just painted on it.

Two individuals, a young person and a girl, both facing towards the center of the image. Their hands converge at the center in a gesture of connection. Above their hands, the word "UNION" is painted. The color palette has predominant hues of pink, blue, yellow, and orange.

Five human figures surrounded by decorative elements like cacti, stars, and clouds on the background. The words "FUERZA," "UNIDAS," and "AMOR" are prominently displayed alongside the figures, translating to "strength," "united," and "love" in English. The mural uses a bright color palette dominated by pinks, blues, oranges, and greens. (Note: "Unidas" is a community mural featuring representations of the women from Nogales, capturing their spirit and stories. Served as a platform for women across Mexico to share their stories).

Two figures wearing face masks that match the background and are seated in front of a circle resembling the sun. The word "JUNTAS" ("together") is displayed above them. One person is wearing glasses and has a tropical-themed shirt. The backdrop has abstract shapes, stars, and plant-like patterns. The artist's signature is visible at the bottom right. Colors: Purple, pink, teal, yellow, green, black, and white.

A young person wearing a blue headscarf, black shirt with the word "RESISTE" ("resist") written on it, and red pants. They stands beside a bicycle, holding onto its handlebars. Surrounding their are large, stylized floral motifs and abstract colorful shapes, including a circular pattern resembling an aura around their head. Colors: Blue, red, yellow, pink, black, and white.

Three figures in a nature setting. On the left, a person with orange hair and is surrounded by large green leaves. In the center, another person with blonde hair crouches beside a large purple fist that rises prominently, adorned with leaves and small berries. This fist, has the word "Quemdonas" written in orange at its base. On the right, a third person with red hair stands in a powerful stance. The background is a solid turquoise color, and the entire scene is infused with bold, contrasting colors, including oranges, reds, greens, and purples.

Two side profiles, one of a person and one of a person, facing in opposite directions. The person's face is on the left, and the person's face is on the right. Both are painted in a blue hue, and they share a background filled with bright, swirling colors such as red, green, yellow, and blue. A pair of pink flowers are located on the person's cheek, which visually connects their faces. The person has a short beard, and both figures appear calm and thoughtful. Behind them, a red circular shape acts as a halo, while beams of light radiate from their eyes. The mural is signed in the bottom right corner by the artist.

A young person with expressive brown eyes. They's depicted holding a bright red heart, surrounded by radiant flora. Two birds fly close, intertwining with the greenery. The ambiance is one of nature. Predominant colors include shades of brown, blue, green, red, and purple, with bursts of yellow and orange.

A monochromatic mural of a person on a red background. their face is in shades of gray, with bright white lines detailing their wavy hair. A crescent moon is depicted near their shoulder, and there's a distinct flower-like mark on their cheek.

The face of a person in shades of pink. their face is detailed, and their lips stand out in a brighter hue. Surrounding their are strawberries, leaves, and decorative elements. The phrase "SABOR A MI TIERRA" is written in ornate, stylized script, which translates to "Flavor of my land". Shades of pink, teal, white, and burgundy dominate.

Two illustrations of Maria Sklodowska Curie. Various symbolic elements like chemical symbols, test tubes, and other references to science are included. The color palette consists of blues, reds, teals, and creams. Text on the mural includes "MARIA SKLODOWSKA CURIE" and references to their being from Poland, France, and their global influence.

Two figures embracing. The figure on the left, whose features are not fully visible, is mostly covered in what appears to be leaves or abstract patterns that blend with the background, creating a surreal effect. The figure on the right, a person with purple hair tied in a bun, is shown with a tear on their cheek. They are wearing a red garment, contrasting with the blue and purple hues of the background. The background features simple outlines of flowers.

column4: DIGNIDAD Y EL DERECHO A VIVIR EN PAZ
column7: A fierce-looking person with deep blue-black hair and intense eyes, having red symbols or marks on their cheeks. They raises one fist, while the other hand touches their collarbone, adorned with leafy tattoos or markings. The background is a combination of soft blue and salmon pink, with a blend of modern and indigenous symbols and patterns. The words "PABELLON B" is displayed. There's also a watermark or signature in the bottom right: "CU CO CA".

A backdrop of green foliage. In the center, a person with curly hair, dressed in a purple shirt, leans on their elbow while writing or drawing on a paper or book. their expression is calm and focused. The table they are working on is covered with a detailed purple tablecloth, featuring floral patterns. On the table, there is a large vase filled with an array of colorful flowers. The flowers are in full bloom, with shades of pink, red, and orange. There are other objects on the table, including a cup of tea. Birds, painted in bright colors, hover near the table. A parrot, with green and red plumage, appears to be pulling at the tablecloth. The background consists of a greenish hue with silhouettes of trees and plants.

Two prominent humanoid faces with exaggerated features are in the center, with blue and yellow colors reminiscent of the sun and the sky. Surrounding them are a myriad of fantastical creatures, symbols, and patterns, from floating animals to expressive hands. The backdrop features elements of nature such as mountains, houses, and a shimmering sun.

A whimsical world where fantastical creatures, humans, and elements of urban and rural life coexist. The depiction consists of a bright and vivid array of colors, illustrating elements such as castles, trains, birds, oversized flowers, horses, humans, and mythical figures all interspersed within a verdant landscape.

A large, ethereal figure, possibly a princess or queen, stands dominantly in the foreground with a crown and flowing long hair. They are surrounded by vividly colored symbols and structures, including a bustling town with whimsically designed houses, flying objects, white humanoid figures, a bright moon, and a lively blue backdrop that suggests both sky and water. The color palette is dominated by deep blues, contrasted with bright oranges, reds, and whites.

column3: Juan Manuel Carmona, Simon Malvaez, Serge Gay Jr, Elliott C Nathan & Christopher Mcutcheon
column7: A collage of faces and figures, dominated by shades of pink, red, and black. There are elements reminiscent of theater and performance, such as curtains and the spotlight effect. Several large faces take center stage, surrounded by an array of smaller illustrations and patterns, suggesting a crowd or audience. (Note: "Showtime, a love letter" is a mural celebrating Queer entertainers and the LGBTQ+ community in San Francisco. Created by five local artists, it represents the diversity and culture of the city's neighborhoods and highlights "Oasis," a venue that serves as a space and platform for the Queer community's expressions and talents. The mural visually narrates the transition from backstage to the main stage, capturing the essence of Queer nightlife and performance).

A large flower bud, the petals open and reveal a swirl of diverse human faces. The background is divided into two main sections: the top half displays classic architectural facades, while the lower half portrays a long perspective of a street or alleyway. Colors: A deep purple background, warm tones of the orange-red flower and colorful depiction of human faces. (Note: The mural "Together we blossom" marks the birth of the world's 8 billionth inhabitant, organized by UNFPA and supported by various local government bodies in Sarajevo. Is dedicated to celebrating new life and is displayed on a school building).

A young person holding a potted plant in one hand and a paint roller in the other. They appears to be painting or refreshing the facade of the building. Below their is a large sneaker that extends to form a slide, complete with directional arrows. Beside the slide is a ladder that extends upward. There's a silhouette of a person at the bottom, seemingly observing or waiting to climb. The mural's bottom bears the text "FASADA FESTIVAL 2021 - TAINE x LAKER." The mural is dominated by blues and earthy tones. The building's blue background contrasts with the warmer colors of the depicted figure, plant, and shoe slide. (Note: "Child of Freedom" highlights the critical role young people play in shaping the future of the world.)

A monochromatic portrait of a person with a pronounced hairstyle and large earrings. The person wears a stylish blouse cinched at the waist with a belt. They stand confidently with their hands on their hips. To the left, a geometric rainbow with the colors of LGBTQ+ pride stands in contrast to the grayscale portrait. A tag at the bottom of the mural reads "@manuel165 #tmpri de2017".

Two children against a bright blue background. On the left side, there's a young Black person with a smile. their left arm is raised, and their hand seems to be playfully covering their head. On the right side, there's a white child wearing aviator goggles and a scarf, who is holding a wooden toy airplane above their head as if they or they are imagining it flying. The mural integrates small, real windows. Dominant colors: bright blue background, brown and beige for the boys' skin tones and the wooden toy airplane, and white for the details such as the boys' teeth and the airplane's propeller.

A profile view of two people, presumably a parent and child/baby, carrying large loads on their backs. Both figures are illustrated in monochromatic black with intricate patterns. They are set against a golden-yellow background that has white sketched clouds and is gradually transitioning to a striped pattern at the bottom. The stripes have a wavy, distorted appearance. The dominant color is a rich golden-yellow, accompanied by the black silhouettes of the figures and the white of the sketched clouds. (Note: Reflects the concerns of indigenous youths who question their forced displacement, lack of educational facilities, and the seizure of their resources and land).

Faces of three children from differebt ethnic backgrounds. Accompanying are words in various languages, all of which translate to "Welcome", such as "welina" (Hawaiian), "Vitajte" (Slovak), "Bienvenido" (Spanish), "Bem-vindo" (Portuguese), "Bienvenue" (French), "Willkommen" (German), "Benvenuto" (Italian), "ΥΡΔΑΤΕ" (Greek word "Υποδοχή"), "dobrodošli" (Serbo-Croatian), "bine ati venit" (Romanian), "Aweh" (South African, often used as a greeting, meaning "hello" or "how are you?"), "Karibu" (Swahili), "Fáilte" (Irish), "Tervetuloa" (Finnish), "groetnis" (Afrikaans). A wide palette including blues, reds, oranges, whites, blacks, pinks, and yellows.

column4: Para Sa Iyo Apo/ "For You Grandson"
column7: Two detailed, monochrome portraits: an older person and a young child. The person is shown with a raised hand, and the young child is depicted leaning on them. The phrase in Filipino "Para Sa Iyo Apo" is written at the top (translated as "For You, Grandma" in English). The monochromatic palette predominantly uses black and white with a background beige. (Note: expresses solidarity with the native Ayta portraying an elderly person, embodying bravery, as they attempts to block the passage of giant trucks and backhoes used for quarrying. The scene captures smoke from the trucks, emphasizing the disruption. The person, carrying their grandson, symbolizes their commitment to defending and fighting for their ancestral land. This piece highlights their determination to secure a prosperous and peaceful future for the next generation).

column4: Para Saan Ang Tapang Mo? / What is your courage for?
column7: The mural features two figures depicted in black and white, bent over in the act of farming or gathering crops. They are dressed in traditional clothing, including wide-brimmed hats that cover their faces. The figures are rendered with detailed lines and shading. The background is a solid yellow color. Above the figures, in red text, is the phrase "PARA SAAN ANG TAPANG MO?" which translates to "What is your courage for?" in English. On the left side of the mural, there is an outline of another figure in white, suggesting an invisible presence.

Features the logo "SMAS" with an image of the Earth being held in cupped hands. The hands appear to be holding water, with a circular recycling symbol underneath made of two fish. Water splashes and flows around the image. Uses shades of blue and white. The hands and Earth are depicted in natural colors.

Two children, person and girl, portrayed in monochromatic blue hues with swirling petals, flowers, and butterflies. The person is reaching out to touch a butterfly. The girl, with an upward gaze, appears to be looking to the butterfly hovering above her.

column4: Rice is not a bullet! "(Rice, Not Bullet! ) (..karugtong na pyesa)
column7: A pair of feet in an exaggerated, textured style. The feet have wrinkles, folds, and calluses. The two pairs of feet are positioned differently: The left pair of feet are depicted as if they are in a walking motion, the toes are pointed slightly downwards, and the feet are elevated off the ground. The right pair of feet are shown flat and facing upwards, as if the person is lying down, with hints of red on some toes, indicating wounds or sores. (Note: dedicated for April One, Anniversary of the Kidapawan Massacre).

A young person with long blond hair is drawing or writing on a windowpane. They have vibrant colors in contrast to the monochromatic skull symbols in the background. The primary colors used are a blend of natural skin tones, blues, and the vibrant hues from the markers the person is using, contrasting with the darker, monochromatic background. (The artwork titled 'Futuro cogido con pinzas' captures the uncertainty of the future of the mining area and the urgent need to seek alternative employment opportunities for future generations).

Various pieces of plastic waste, such as bags and straws, arranged to form a bird-like figure. The bird is positioned inside a shopping basket. Colors: mostly muted, with blues and whites being prominent due to the plastic bags, and touches of red and green.
An orange, wrapped with black bands that have clasps, placed on plastic waste resembling a boat. Colors: Orange, black, blue, and multiple colors from the plastic waste.
A large, old-fashioned train in grayscale, surrounded by architecture and figures also in grayscale. The elements are integrated with the actual windows and structures of the building.

A large fish made entirely out of what appears to be crushed and folded green and silver cans, created from recycled materials. The fish seems to be floating in mid-air, with its shadow cast on the pavement below. The colors of the fish are predominantly green, with white, red, and silver accents, likely from the labels on the cans. The background consists of a yellow wall, and a gray lower section of the wall, with the pavement below being tiled in gray and red.

A sequence of painted fruits (strawberry, cherry, pineapple slice, olive, orange, and apple) on window shutters, each occupying one section of the shutters. Each section uses colors to represent each type of fruit such as red for the strawberry and cherry, and orange for the orange.

A child is playing with an origami paper bird in one building. The child is seated and wearing colorful clothing and is positioned close to the ground, with knees bent and arms extended forward, holding the paper bird. The child is also wearing a cap and sunglasses, adding to the playful and casual feel of the scene. In the other building an origami bird appears to be in motion, as if it's flying. There is a shadow on the wall that emphasizes the bird's flight path, giving a three-dimensional effect.The bird is colorful, matching the vibrant and playful theme of the mural.
A fish’s head that merges into crumpled plastic waste towards its tail side. Various natural colors for the fish, such as browns and greys, and colors like green and yellow for the plastic waste.

A fish wrapped in plastic, positioned vertically. The fish's body is detailed, with scales and a visible eye, but it is tightly encased in a crumpled plastic material, which is drawn in greyish tones with highlights reflecting light. The lower part of the fish, near the tail, is wrapped in a different material or perhaps stained, shown in a brownish-yellow hue.
Above the fish, there is a recycling symbol drawn in black. The mural is set against a neutral-colored background of the building's exterior, which consists of light-colored bricks. The background is mostly beige, with sections in grey and brown. At the bottom of the mural, the artist's name is visible in orange text.

A close-up of a person's neck and hands. The skin is rendered in shades of grey, with red highlights that appear on the hands and parts of the neck against the monochrome background. The figure's left hand is shown gripping the neck, with elongated fingers, some of which are smeared with red. The person appearing to have been hurt by a stick that is pressing against their neck. The figure's left hand is gripping the neck as if in pain, and there are red marks on the hands and neck that suggest injury. The words "I WAS HERE" are inscribed on the lower part of the neck, just above the collarbone. The artist's name is visible in white text in the top right corner of the mural.

column4: Pula ang Kulay ng Saya / "The Color of Joy is Red"
column7: An array of intertwined firearms. The pieces depicted include revolvers and rifles all entangled in a complex, dense arrangement that covers the entire visible surface of the wall. The color palette is primarily monochromatic, with shades of brown, rust, and black dominating.

column4: Game over? (When the people burned tires in order to prevent warplanes from bombing)
column7: The completed tic-tac-toe game shows X's represented as stylized airplanes, which suggests a military theme. The O's are standard circles. The game appears to have ended in a draw. There are three main colors: black for the tic-tac-toe grid and hashtagged phrase "#GAME OVER", red for the airplanes and the artist's signature or tag, and the natural color of the wall's surface as the background.

column4: Learn to love first (A little girl teaches a soldier an important lesson, how to use their heart before they uses their weapon)
column7: Two contrasting figures: on the left, a white silhouette of a young child reaching out to touch or draw a red heart on an easel; on the right, a seated soldier in full gear, facing away from the child and appearing disengaged from the child's action. Color: black for the figures and the beam, white for the child's silhouette, red for the heart, and black for the soldier, set against the neutral background of the wall.

column4: Syria is lost (A painting adapted from Banksy's work)
column7: A stencil artwork of a person depicted in black on the edge of a broken piece of wall, reaching out towards a red balloon in the shape of a heart, which is floating away and detached from their hand. The scene is set against a backdrop of rubble and decay. The color palette is minimal, with the person in black, the heart-shaped balloon in red.

column4: International Children's Day (Five drawings that show the suffering of Syrian children)
column7: Five circular illustrations each depicting different scenes. From left to right: 1. A person in a red shirt and blue pants kneels on the ground near a large vehicle (possibly a UN vehicle) working with tools. The background is mostly white with a few small details. 2. A dark silhouette of a child stands in a barren landscape with a red sky, observing a scene of destruction with multiple bombs falling from the sky and debris scattered around, including a broken bicycle. 3. A child in a yellow dress stands with arms raised towards the sky in a red and orange background, where several missiles are depicted pointing upwards, resembling ominous figures. 4. A person with crutches, missing one leg, holds a child who also appears to be missing legs. The background is blue, with a city skyline in ruins and smoke rising, indicating destruction. 5. A person in a blue shirt and grey shorts is jumping in the air, playing with a soccer ball on a green field. However, the red spot on their back, suggests they have been shot. Above the images is the hashtag written in Arabic: "#أنا_طفل" which translates to "#I_am_a_child". Each circle is bordered in black, and the overall background of the mural is white. The colors used are vivid, with each scene dominated by different shades.

column4: Civil defense teams rescued civilians from under the rubble
column7: A bearded person with angel wings and a halo, dressed in a jacket with patches, carrying a child. They are standing among rubble and debris, with a broken soccer ball and a teddy bear visible in the wreckage. The sky behind them is a solid blue. Arabic script is visible above the figures. The text at the top of the image reads: "وَمَنْ أَحْيَاهَا فَكَأَنَّمَا أَحْيَا النَّاسَ جَمِيعًا", which translates to: "And whoever saves a life, it is as though they had saved all mankind." This is a verse from the Quran (Surah Al-Ma'idah, 5:32). The color palette has a dominant blue for the sky, varied tones in the figure’s attire, and grey and brown hues for the rubble.

column4: Elections for Bashar al-Assad in 2021 (participating in the elections means participating in the bombing)
column7: A fragmented piece of wall. The upper portion is painted white, while the lower portion is blue with a black silhouette of a city skyline with several tall buildings. Above the skyline, bombs are depicted falling towards the city from the blue sky. At the top, there is an outstretched hand dropping what appears to be a ballot. The text on the card appears to be written in Arabic. It says "الانتخابات" (al-intikhabat), which translates to "Elections" in English. The image depicts a mural painted on a broken piece of concrete, possibly part of a destroyed building.

An array of flowers and a dragonfly. The flowers are oversized and occupy the entire space, with various species represented. A prominent dragonfly is depicted on the right side, and a distinct red insect is on one of the flowers in the lower portion. The building's features, like windows, are incorporated into the mural.

A monochromatic mural depicting a complex industrial scene. It's filled with mechanical structures, ductwork, and various undefined machinery. Several human figures are integrated into the machinery, some appearing entwined or fused with the mechanical elements. The perspective is isometric and rendered in grayscale, with the use of black, white, and various shades of gray.

A fish that appears to be bursting through the wall. Its mouth is open, as if gasping for air. The fish is partially enveloped by crumpled plastic, giving the impression that it's trapped by the plastic. In the upper left corner, there's a recycling symbol. The colors are naturalistic, with shades of gray, silver, white, and touches of yellow around the eye of the fish. The crumpled plastic is depicted in various shades of white and gray.

An octopus with tentacles extended out of a large crumpled piece of blue plastic. The octopus is depicted in naturalistic shades of brown and purple, while the plastic is a translucent blue, and the background is a flat peach or pale orange.

Close-up of two human eyes, with the left eye appearing youthful and the right showing the wrinkles and signs of age of an elderly person. There's a distinction between the two sides, suggesting a transition from youth to old age. The colors used are monochromatic, primarily shades of gray and black with subtle touches of white.

column3: Dante (Assistants: Sandro Tsitskishvili, George Kalandarishvili, Alexander Kvantaliani, Acho Khutsishvili, Lizi Tsitskishvili, Tornike Melikidze)
column7: The mural features an antelope in motion, seemingly leaping across a geometric background that resembles a basketball court. The background is composed of various rectangles and partial circles, with colors like green, orange, and yellow, and shades of blue and teal. The antelope's body is positioned diagonally, its head turned as if looking back, with its legs extended in mid-stride. The color palette of the antelope includes earth tones—browns, tans, white, and black.

A bird's head wearing headphones. The bird's beak is closed but dripping paint. The artwork features a mix of bold colors including yellow for the bird's head, red, blue, and yellow for the beak, and shades of gray and white for the headphones.

A large horse in mid-gallop, its body and legs extended as if in motion. The horse appears superimposed over a background that resembles a beach with horizontal stripes, while small cars on a road occupy the lower portion of the image. The horse is rendered in shades of brown and black, while the background consists of beige, representing sand, and blue, representing the sky or sea. The cars are depicted in red, white, and blue. (Note: Artwork for the Tbilisi Mural Fest in 2019, depicting the backend of a racehorse to highlight the horse racing industry, which supports a diverse range of jobs including jockeys, stable workers, and veterinarians. It underscores the industry's role in providing sustainable economic opportunities).

Athletes engaged in various sports. From left to right: a volleyball player, a runner, a basketball player, a soccer player, and a cyclist. The athletes are in action poses, with the basketball player, a person with a visible muscular build, being the most prominent. The other figures display dynamic motion indicative of their respective sports. The background transitions from a warm yellow and orange on the left to a cooler blue on the right. The athletes are painted in naturalistic tones.

Composite scene with a large profile of a person's face on the right side. Within the outline of their hair and facial features, a smaller scene depicting a rural landscape with a donkey and two figures, presumably farmers, one of whom- a person - is guiding the donkey.

Agricultural life, focusing on a person tending to grapevines. On the left, a profile of a face made out of grapevine elements, merging with the scene. The phrase "Manos que logran vida" translates to "Hands that achieve life". A palette of greens, representing the grape leaves, with purples and yellows for the grapes and background elements.

Two anthropomorphic creatures with the heads of llamas and the bodies of humans, dressed in elaborate, colorful garments and stand back-to-back, each holding an object—a blue orb and a pink crystal. Above them is a rainbow arching from one side to the other. The rainbow seems a symbol of LGBT+ pride and diversity. The artwork has a light blue background, the multicolored rainbow, and the llamas' attire featuring purples, blues, yellows, and greens.

Two anthropomorphic figures with equine heads and human bodies, positioned in a mirror image, sharing a heart against a backdrop of radiating multicolored rays resembling the colors of the LGBT+ pride flag. Colors: A diverse palette, including the multicolored rainbow patterns, along with pinks, blues, greens, and purples for the figures' clothing.

This image shows a mural with a "Thank You" message in the center, surrounded by colorful patterns that include swirls and rainbow motifs. Within circular frames are portraits of individuals, each labeled with roles: "Social Worker," "Trash Collector," "Delivery People," and "Grocer." These roles likely represent various essential workers. The colors are vivid and encompass nearly all hues of the rainbow.

A person in work using an helmet, seemingly engaged in a laborious task. They are leaning forward, appearing to exert great effort, with their hands gripping a large, heavy weight. their facial expression suggests strain, and their posture reflects the physical exertion involved. The mural is set against a metal door and industrial surroundings, with a sign on the door to the left reading "FORCE 7500 kg INTERDIT AUX PERSONNES".

A series of figures (men) in various upside-down and right-side-up poses creating a visual sequence that suggests motion or dance. The figures are rendered in a monochromatic palette, which contrasts with the wall's weathered texture. Their poses range from standing to crouching, with some appearing to be in mid-movement, as if caught during a performance or exercise.

Four figures in white shirts and dark pants, each wearing a hat, appear to be hanging from a large, twisted wire or barbed line as if they are trapped or suspended, unable to move freely. They seem to be helplessly dangling as if they are on display, much like clothing on a hanger. The figures are depicted in a monochromatic color scheme, blending into the grayscale background.

Grayscale painting of a young person leaning out of a dark doorway, appearing to be taking a break from work, as suggested by their attire and the tool in hand. The person is wiping their brow, which indicates exhaustion or a pause from labor. At the bottom of the doorway, there are what appear to be crushed cans, hinting at waste or discarded items. Adjacent to the doorway is a rusted metal door with the word "CRIN" written on it, likely a form of graffiti.

Two monochromatic figures, a person and a person, each occupying a separate recessed window space in a wall. Both are sitting with their knees drawn up to their chests, holding coin purses, and appear to be counting the coins. The person seems to have fewer coins compared to the man. In front of each figure, there are stacks of red objects that appear to be plastic cups or possibly candles. The figures are depicted in grayscale, in contrast the red objects and the surrounding wall, which is a muted beige or brown.

Two red-toned figures, each with an elephant head merging into their own. The elephants' trunks are intertwined above the figures, symbolizing a connection between them. The figures are submerged in water or a wave-like design, with green and blue hues swirling around. One of the figures holds a small blue bowl, while the other uses a long stick or spoon to stir something in the bowl. The background features a rising sun, and the water seems to blend into the horizon. The colors primarily consist of reds, purples, greens, and blues. (Note: A mother pouring knowledge onto their daughter, celebrating the value of transferring wisdom and traditions from one generation to the next, emphasizing the importance of preserving what we inherit).

column4: We are from Water and from £arth
column7: A figure, with two visible hands, cradling a baby in the arms, both rendered in shades of blue. The surrounding environment also incorporates blue tones, creating a unified color scheme. In the white background, there is a silhouette of birds in flight, drawn in a lighter blue. A small, green object, possibly a boat, is visible on the right side, providing a contrast against the dominant blue color. At the top of the blue area that forms part of the figure, there also appears to be a hint of green, suggesting the presence of vegetation.

column4: Dizzy Gillespie " Art is not a crime"
column7: A person playing a trumpet, standing above children who are reading books on a floating platform that appears to be a tree root or a piece of land with tendrils or roots extending downward. The background features a blue sky with clouds. The colors include earth tones for the figures and the floating platform, with blues for the sky. (Note: The "Education Is Not A Crime" campaign emphasizing the connection among global communities facing oppression. It aims to raise awareness about the discrimination against Iranian Baha'is, by also addressing inequality and discrimination worldwide. The initiative advocates for a universal approach to fighting injustice).

Juxtaposition of a human profile and a rhinoceros head merging into one another. A geometric shape, specifically a red triangle, intersects the two profiles. The background is a simple blue, which contrasts with the red geometric figure and complements the gray tones used for the profiles.

column4: Almócita contra la violencia de género
column7: A person's face with a sorrowful expression. Two large scrolls or lists with names, and between them, a statement in Spanish reads "Almohada contra la violencia de género" (translates to "A pillow against gender violence"). The lists may represent the names of victims or survivors of gender-based violence. Additionally, silhouettes of people can be seen between the scrolls. The colors are muted, with the person's face in grayscale against the cream-colored background of the scrolls.

column4: Comissions..."Existen pocas armas en el mundo tan poderosas como una niña con un libro en la mano"
column7: A young person reading a book. Above their head, a thought bubble contains various symbols representing different school subjects or areas of knowledge, such as science, mathematics, and art. The background features silhouettes of people with a gender equality symbol, indicating a diverse group. The text on the book they are holding reads, "Por un futuro entre iguales" (translates to "For a future among equals") and further text states "La educación no cambia el mundo, cambia a las personas que van a cambiar el mundo" ("Education does not change the world, it changes the people who are going to change the world". The colors are varied and vibrant, mainly with with green, yelow and orange.

A young child and an adult person are separated by barbed wire. The child, dressed in a pink and white striped shirt, reaches out with an expression of fear, while the person, with a distressed look on their face, extends their arm. The background is pale.

An array of wildlife, with the central image being a stag with a prominent set of antlers that frame a forest and river scene. Alongside the stag, there are portraits of other animals, including an owl and a boar, depicted with a high level of detail and realism. These animals are presented in front of the natural landscape. The colors are natural and earthy, with rich browns, greens, and blues.

column4: Mujer es poder / Woman is power
column7: An elderly person holding a dog. The phrase "mujer es poder" (translating to "woman is power") is displayed on the left. The figures are in grayscale against a yellow backdrop, along with the brown and maroon decorative elements.

A group of individuals from diverse backgrounds, with a range of expressions from thoughtful to joyful. The artwork features a stylized, illustrative technique with strong outlines and textured shading. Below the figures, there is a phrase in Spanish that reads, "Luchamos por el mundo arcoíris," (translates to "We fight for the rainbow world"). This phrase, accompanied by the rainbow stripe, suggests advocacy for inclusivity and diversity, commonly associated with the LGBT+ movement.

A close-up portrait of a person wearing a hat. The person's face is rendered in monochrome, contrasting with the geometric, colorful background pattern that includes a depiction of a pineapple. To the left, the words "Llamada de la Tierra" are written (translating to "Call of the Earth" in English).

column4: La guerra no es un juego
column7: A child smiling and playing with what appears to be a toy tank, the child and the toy are depicted in grayscale against a light background. Accompanying the image is the Spanish phrase "la guerra no es un juego," (translates to "war is not a game"). The colors are monochromatic.

Andean Condor with its wool made up of dripping lines and patterns. The colors are monochromatic, primarily using black and white with shades of gray. (Note: Highlights the critical conservation status of the Andean Condors in Colombia, where their numbers are decreasing due to human impact).

A person in a cowboy hat with a smile. In the foreground, two large hands are holding a pile of green beans or peas, which seem to be spilling over the edges. The colors are predominantly green for the beans, earth tones for the hands, black and white for the portrait of the person, and additional black, green, yellow, and blue in the graphic elements around the portrait.

A child smiling created with bold black strokes on a backdrop of alternating yellow and black stripes. Words are etched across the face: "Educación es Equidad" (Education is Equity). The color scheme uses black and yellow for the background stripes, which frame and highlight the child's face and the white text.

Fragmented geometric patterns with realistic depictions of a person's face. The face appears multiple times across the mural, rendered in black and white, with varying degrees of visibility, some parts obscured by the overlapping shapes. The man’s expression seems intense with one image showing their holding their hand near their face. The background is divided into blocks of red, black, gray, and white.

A large red rake against a background filled with grey industrial machinery and debris. Between the tines of the rake, small green plants are sprouting. The colors are predominantly red for the rake, various shades of grey for the machinery, and green for the plants.

A large mechanized figure with a humanoid face connected to an array of industrial pipes and apparatuses. The figure's eyes are depicted as red. It is wearing a gas mask, with various pipes and tubes connected to it, and smoke and pollution are being emitted from the machinery attached to its head. The figure appears to be looking down at a smartphone in its hand. The palette is muted, with shades of gray, green, and beige dominating the scene.
An array of various vehicles, and possibly robot parts, all entangled in a jumbled heap. The color palette is limited, dominated by greys and whites.

An anthropomorphic fish-headed figure dressed in a uniform, adorned with a red beret. The figure is surrounded by other marine elements, suggesting a fusion of human and aquatic life. The colors are varied, with the red of the beret, the blues of the water and uniform, and the various hues of the marine life.

A large broom is sweeping up a collection of small, dark grey robotic-like figures. The broom is painted in bright red with a yellow top, and it is positioned on a tiled floor that reflects the figures and objects around it. To the left, there is a large hand with a gold rings on the ring finger, emerging from a grassy area. The grass is painted in various shades of green, with a texture that contrasts with the smooth surface of the tiles. Behind the hand, a large slipper with a plaid pattern in blue, green, and white is partially visible, 
To the right, there is a red signature by the artist.

Sprawling green plants with numerous leaves and a bright central flower at the top. The flower is white and yellow, radiating a glowing light. The green plants appear to be growing over a backdrop that resembles a complex industrial system, rendered in shades of purple and gray. The scene includes various elements, such as buildings, structures, and mechanical or electronic components. Some small figures are scattered throughout the cityscape, and a statue of a horse-mounted figure is visible on the right side of the mural. (Note: titled "Emer(gentes)" features botanical motifs, wildflowers, and weeds. The artist emphasizes the focus on garden weeds, as the plants capable of breaking through concrete with patience. Used metaphorically to convey a symbol of hope and change, suggesting that even in tough conditions, growth and transformation are possible).

A large, anthropomorphic fish-like creature seated in a contemplative pose, with human-like arms and legs, resting in an underwater environment. Above it, a fishing hook looms, while a smaller creature with a shell observes from below. The colors are vibrant, with a rich palette of blues, greens, and oranges that create a lively underwater scene. (Note: The artwork presents two interpretations: one highlighting the environmental harm done to oceans and the other depicting individual vulnerability within society's constraints).

A giant creature covered in green fur, resembling a mix between a plant and an animal. The creature has a gentle and friendly appearance, with a broad face, expressive eyes, and large curled horns on its head. It is seated, taking up most of the wall, with its large feet resting on the ground. In its hand, it holds a tiny human figure, a young person dressed in red and white, who is holding a small stuffed toy. The person seems to be looking up at the creature. The background includes a few small trees and rocks, emphasizing the peaceful and natural setting. (Note: Explores the relationship between new generations and Mother Nature, suggesting that young people could be our hope in halting the environmental destruction caused by humanity).

A surreal figure seated at a desk, resembling a humanoid insect or alien. The figure is dressed in a formal green suit and is seated in a red chair. Its head is adorned with multiple bulbous eyes and long, protruding antennae and two horns. The figure holds a pen in one hand, as if writing or signing a document, while the other hand rests on the desk. The background is a mix of green tones, with framed pictures behind the figure and abstract elements.

Artwork spread across multiple vertical panels, depicting an elderly person, likely a fisherperson, holding what appears to be fishing tools—possibly a trident-like spear. The figure is rendered in earth tones such as browns and beiges. The gaze of the individual is directed toward the task at hand. The background suggests that the person is on a boat, with the sea behind them.

Portrays a person resting on the ground, seemingly in a state of sleep or exhaustion, covered by a thin material and with a "RECYCLE" plastic bag prominently displayed nearby. The color scheme consists primarily of subdued blues, grays, and browns, with contrasting touches of white and the green of the plastic bag, set against a dark red and black background.

A person in a red shirt wielding a tool, set against a backdrop that incorporates actual building features, such as windows and air conditioners. The mural is overlaid with lush green leaves that seem to grow from the real foliage at the building's base. (Note: "Organics," serves as a reminder to the residents that they are integral parts of a larger whole within the microcosm of their neighborhood).

A person, likely a farmer, standing and holding a pitchfork. The figure is dressed in overalls and a checkered shirt with rolled-up sleeves, with a red cap on their head, looking off to the side. The background includes elements that resemble grasses and plants. In the corner, there appears to be a table. The mural is painted on a tall cylindrical structure, like a silo.

A person sitting at a desk, writing with a quill pen, which suggests a vintage setting. They are dressed in an modest outfit, with their hair styled in a neat updo. The scene around their is filled with various objects: a globe, several books, a teacup, and a vase with flowers. There's a detailed botanical illustration leaning against a book, and an open box with letters inside. The mural is set against the backdrop of a building, with windows above the desk area, blending the artwork into the actual architecture. The colors are soft and muted.

An elderly person with grey hair and a young girl, both engaged in a symbolic exchange. The elderly person is dressed in a light-colored blouse, has their arm around the young girl, who is wearing a sleeveless top. The person holds a small, blue globe in their hands, symbolizing the Earth. The elderly person is holding an hourglass, which they are presenting to the girl. The background is a soft beige, blending with the building's architecture.

The mural shows several figures, mostly women, dressed in garments of green, blue, and red. The figures appear to be interacting with each other, with some extending their arms and hands toward one another. The figures are depicted in a continuous line across the wall. The colors are muted and earthy, with the background of the mural being a soft grey. (Note: Community as unity, as a celebration of differences and shared values, recognizing that each individual is essential for maintaining the balance of the whole).

Three figures (possibly women) standing side by side, each dressed in a loose, oversized shirt in different solid colors—blue, light brown, and green. The figures are depicted with their arms outstretched, holding a long, curved piece of string or rope that connects them. Their faces are not visible, as they are either turned away from the viewer or obscured. The background is composed of a brick wall. The overall color scheme is muted and earthy.

Two men, each holding a circular object that features an illustration of a person's face surrounded by intricate patterns. The person on the left holds an object with a blue face and patterns, while the person on the right holds one with a red face and patterns. Colors: blue and red of the circular objects against the orange background.

A series of scenes spread across three horizontal levels, portraying people dressed in traditional clothing, engaged in rural or pastoral activities in a mountainous landscape. At the top, two people stand on a rocky terrain, dressed in traditional attire, including long white shirts and shawls. They appear to be in conversation, walking together with one person gesturing with their hand as they navigate the rocky landscape. Two other figures are depicted but not entirely visible. In the middle scene, six figures. One stands with their back to the viewer, holding a staff and gazing into the distance, another is seated on the ground. The background showcases a mountain range. Below people are seated on the ground, facing each other. The people are draped in shawls and skirts, and they appear to be in contemplation or conversation. A sheep is grazing nearby. The backdrop continues to feature the mountain landscape, with a peak in the distance. The scenes have soft earth-toned, with greens, browns, blues, and neutral shades of the figures' clothing.

Three people positioned side by side. The left person is dressed in a red dress with long sleeves. They stand with a contemplative expression, gazing off into the distance. The central person is dressed in a white blouse with lace trim and a yellow shawl draped over their shoulders. They holds a spear upright. their expression is serious and determined, directly facing the viewer. The person on the right, dressed in a dark teal garment, stands with their back mostly to the viewer. They holds a rolled piece of paper behind their back, possibly symbolizing a hidden plan, secret knowledge, or the importance of communication. Each person representing different shades of red, yellow, and blue against the pale background.

Two people embracing each other. The person on the left has their head adorned with large green leaves, while the person on the right has flowers in their hair. Additionally, on top of the head of the person on the right, there is a small, diminutive figure of a person waçking. The people on the right is dressed in green, which complements the natural elements in their hair. The overall color scheme is dominated by greens, browns, and floral hues, against the warm yellow background.

column4: You go your way, I’ll go your way too
column7: A person's face, looking sideways. Next to the person is a large dog, possibly a wolf, with its head close. In the foreground, there's a hand holding a bird, with other birds around, and flowers at the bottom. There is also text on the mural and a silhouette of a person with a dog. The color palette is dominated by cool tones, with purples and blues, and touches of white and pink that add contrast and visual interest.

A young person sitting among three wolves in various poses. The setting seems to be outdoors with elements of foliage in the background. Color predominance of cool greens and greys. The human figure contrasts with the wolves through the use of lighter skin tones and a black outfit.

An octopus, with its tentacles spread out across the wall. The head of the octopus is centrally located, and its tentacles extend outwards. The octopus is in shades of black and white, with hints of pink and blue on the head.
A human face in profile, black and white against a deeply blue background, with a bird, seemingly lifeless, placed at the human mouth. The color blue dominates.

The word "MIGRANTS" written in large, blue capital letters, with a structure that resembles a roof above the text. Below the text, resting against the baseline as if it were the ground, is a figure wrapped in a blanket, in a sleeping or exhausted posture. The color blue is used for the text and the outline of the roof, a neutral background.

A person carrying a large basket on their head adorned with a colorful pattern. their attire and the way they carries the basket suggest a cultural practice of carrying goods, which is common in many parts of Africa and other regions around the world. The color palette includes earthy tones and some colors on the basket and headscarf.

Two smiling children. Above and around the children are colorful, oversized vegetables and fruits, such as carrots, broccoli, mushrooms, strawberries, and eggplant. These items are floating in the sky, which is painted in bright blue with green clouds. On the left side of the mural, a text reads: "Welcome to Cornerstone Road Gardens, home of Veggies on the Sprouts." The words are written in various colors. The children are depicted in earthy tones, with the person on the left having braided hair and the person on the right having a bald head. The bottom features a green field.

A young child reading a book. The child is seated at a desk cluttered with various colored pencils and papers, focusing on the book. There is a pair of adult hands holding the book open. The child is also holding a blue pen or pencil in their right hand. The colors in the image are subdued, with the child's red shirt in contrast against the darker background.

A young person deeply focused on a laptop screen, which illuminates their face in a lit setting at night. The light from the laptop screen casts a glow on their features. The color palette is subdued, with the contrasting elements of the bright laptop screen and the darker surrounding environment. (Note: created at the Polytechnic University of Valencia, depicts a student studying through the night to aptures a familiar experience for many students—pulling an all-nighter to study without sleep).

A young person sitting on the ground, surrounded by a number of open books. They are holding a small toy, which they are looking at. The person is wearing glasses, and their posture and environment suggest a setting of learning and play. The colors are soft and somewhat muted.

A person, dressed in dark clothing, is walking with a hunched posture. They are pulling a cart or garbage bag, which is filled with some items. Attached to their arms and eventually to the cart are numerous colorful balloons, tethered by strings. These balloons appear to be floating behind them. The balloons are depicted in vibrant colors. The mural captures a sense of struggle as the person leans forward, exerting effort to move the items she's carrying.

Paintings on three cylindrical silos, featuring three farmers engaging in agricultural work at different stages of labor, from tilling the land to gathering the wheat sheaves. The background landscape extends across the silos, creating a panorama of the fields they work in. The color palette is natural and earthy, with the browns of the soil and the golden hues of the wheat.

column3: Aravani Art Project: Lead Artists: Purushi, Poornima Sukumar, Sadhna Prasad; Team Members: Liyafat Ali, Mohammad Hussain, Nayantara Joseph, Arif, Akmal, Maithri, Udhaya
column4: Indru Namadhai. Today belongs to us.
column7: Several smiling human faces each adorned in clothing with bright, bold patterns. The image features a colorful mural with the text "TODAY BELONGS TO US" prominently displayed at the top. (Note: reflects the spirit of Coimbatore's people, using colors and patterns inspired by the city to celebrate community and togetherness).

Multiple human figures engaged in various activities. The central figures appear to be people adorned in traditional attire, interacting joyfully. The surroundings are embellished with bold patterns and floral motifs, and there is text in a non-Latin script, possibly Tamil, indicative of a cultural context. The color palette is bright and diverse.

column3: Aravani Art Project with Chifumi Krohom. Lead Artists: Raina, Sandeepta Das, Amrita, Neha, Diyasa, Sadhna Prasad, Poornima Sukumar. Team Members: Adrija, Aanup Acharya, Upasana, Nandini, Khushbu Agrawal, Stuti Agarwal, Saurav Ghosh, Anish Saraogi, Lovely Sharma, Pranjal Jain, Sejuti Malakar, Dr Soma Roy, Dr. Jaana, Mr. Pinto
column4: Who am I? Know me! I exist.
