column7: A mural painted on the side of a building showng a portrait of a person with an earnest expression alongside a colored bird in flight. The background has geometric patterns and a multicolored design. The color palette is varied.

Coloured mural painted on the façade of a wave-roofed building. It shows a street scene with people and urban elements, with figures engaged in everyday activities such as walking, cycling, chatting, selling goods, and playing music. Vehicles like buses or tuk-tuks appear next to market stalls and street signs, indicating a community or neighbourhood setting. The mural uses strong contrasting colours — red, blue, yellow, green, and pink. Trees can be seen behind the building.

Scenes of everyday life with various individuals engaged in different activities. A person is hanging laundry, a child is playing with a dog, a person is sitting with their phone, and other individuals appear to be in conversation or contemplation. The artwork is set against a backdrop of a building with multiple windows. The color palette is diverse and bright.

A street scene with various human individuals depicted in a range of activities: a person on a balcony, a person with a child, another person riding a scooter, and a person with balloons. The text in the mural, written in Devanagari script, suggests a cultural context likely in India.The color palette is vivid and diverse.

The phrase "GENDER FREE" is presented in large letters, with a backdrop of diverse hands raised together within a colorful circle. Accompanying images include roses and the faces of individuals. The color palette is varied.

A person's face with a focused expression, partially obscured by a respirator mask, commonly used in street art for protection against paint fumes. The mask covers their nose and mouth. Surrounding their head are soft, flowing green and white leaves. The background features a gradient of earthy tones, transitioning from a light beige on the left to a greenish hue on the right, complementing the foliage around their head. The mural is signed by the artist on the right side.
A young child sleeping against a cosmic backdrop, filled with stars and nebulae. The color palette is dominated by cool blues and purples, typical of nighttime and space imagery.

A large, expressive face of a person, rendered primarily in shades of blue. The person appears to be screaming or shouting, with their mouth wide open, displaying their teeth. The use of blue dominates the entire image. The background transitions from darker shades of blue on the left to lighter tones on the right, blending into the figure. The artist's name along with "Prison Ink 2017," is written in the lower left corner, also in blue.

A young person's head, which appears to be duplicated, with a transparent or blue overlay slightly offset from the original head. This gives the impression of a dual or layered presence. The person's face occupy most of the upper section. Below them, there are blue satellite dishes, with one prominently centered and pointed skyward. their expression is calm and introspective, with their eyes gently closed and their head slightly tilted. The colors predominantly used are shades of blue and warm skin tones, creating a contrast between the cool, technological elements below and the soft, human expression above. The background has hints of pink and peach. The artist's name, are inscribed at the top right of the mural. The predominant colors are warm skin tones, light blues, and pinks, enhancing the sense of depth and complexity in the mural.

Three baboons with their eyes blindfolded, ears covered, and mouths muzzled (reminiscent of the proverbial principle "see no evil, hear no evil, speak no evil"). They are caged, and around the cage are instruments such as a microphone, a harmonica, and a book. The color palette is brown with touches of brighter colors.

A large crumpled red plastic bottle lying horizontally across the wall. The bottle shows the creases and folds that result from it being crushed. A polar bear is lying inside the bottle. Emerging from the neck of the bottle is a straw. The background is a light blue color.

The image displays a mural that blends elements of nature and urbanization. It depicts a pile of colorful rocks or possibly discarded items resembling a hill, with people in boats navigating the waters around it. The background features a sky with a gradient from yellow to pink, with silhouettes of buildings that fade into the sky, and a central, realistic column that could be part of the building where the mural is painted, integrating actual windows into the artwork. The color palette is varied in the lower section, with more muted and pastel tones in the sky.

A young person standing atop a pile of books stacked within a small boat, which is itself afloat on a sea of clothing. The boy, with a halo-like circle behind their head, is peering into the distance. The color palette has earth tones, contrasting with the colorful but disordered clothing below.

A young person seated on the ground, their head in their hands, with a sense of despair or sorrow. Next to their is a discarded or thrown away doll and a crumpled piece of paper. The color palette is muted with the exception of the red dress.

A person standing alone, wearing a long, flowing blue dress. their appearance is melancholic, with large, expressive eyes that convey a sense of longing. The girl's long black hair, with hints of green, is blown to the side as if caught by a breeze. They clutches tightly to a colorful patchwork doll in their arms, holding it close to their chest. The doll is colored. The ground beneath their is scattered with books, some open and some closed. The background features a gradient of warm tones, with orange at the top and fading into a bright yellow as it approaches the ground.

column4: Sailing in the sea of books, duelling knowledgement and reaching paradise
column7: A scene with a large, colorful figure that resembles a teddy bear, with a patterned body and X's for eyes. In front of this figure, there is a boat with four children, floating on a sea of books. The color palette is vivid, with the figure and the books rendered in a multitude of colors against subdued tones of the boat and the children.

A figure, likely a girl, from the back, with their hair flowing in the wind. They are wearing a dress made of an assortment of colorful books, while three teddy bears seem to be flying around them. The color is varied, with warm hues of the blocks in contrast to the bright yellow background.

Two children. The foreground features a person looking up, while a person stands on a stack of books with a smartphone in their hand. Color palette: green wall in contrast to the muted tones of the children's clothing and the books.

column4: Se navegar é preciso, ‘Esperança’ é o meu barco
column7: A child sitting in a boat that appears to be floating on a sea of colorful clothes. The child seems to be holding a teddy bear. The backdrop, with a window and what looks like falling stars. The color palette is a mix of the muted tones of the boat and window against the varied colors of the clothes.

column4: A alegria de ter está em dividir
column7: Two characters, one wearing a rabbit-like costume and the other in a panda costume, in front of a large circular object in yellow. The rabbit figure is reaching out towards the panda, who is holding what appears to be a teddy bear with colorful patterns. The background is vibrant red with the circular orange shape.

Two tall stacks of books, each supporting a figure at the top. On the left stack, a person in a red dress is standing, while on the right stack, a boy, dressed in shades of blue, is sitting and reading a book. The stacks of books rise from a pile of colorful books at the bottom, in front of a building with multiple windows. The stacks of books are composed of various colors, including blue, red, yellow, green, and purple. The books at the bottom form a colorful pile, with shades of red, blue, pink, and yellow, among others. The background wall of the building is a light, beige color.

Multiple figures lounging and intertwined on an ornate, Victorian-style sofa. The people are depicted in identical clothing, featuring a bold blue geometric pattern against their monochromatic skin, which is painted in shades of gray. The color palette is dominated by cool tones, with the stark blue patterns in contrast to the grayscale of the people. It has also splashes of pink and blue in the background.

Two polar bears on either side of a flagpole, with the phrase "MASSIVE SOCIAL UNREST?" written across. The background features geometric patterns in shades of blue and white, evoking the icy habitats of polar bears. The bears are portrayed in mid-roar.

A person looking back over their shoulder, carrying a stick across their back. Hanging from the stick are several figures that appear to be birds in shades of blue. The person herself is depicted in shades of blue and gray, with intricate patterns on their clothing. The background is a mix of colors, including orange, blue, pink, and yellow, with abstract shapes and textures. The artist's signature is visible in the upper left corner.

A profile of a person against a background inscribed with the words "Liberté, Égalité, Fraternité," which is the national motto of France translating to "Liberty, Equality, Fraternity." These principles reflect the values of the French Revolution. The mural includes a section of text that appears as a handwritten list, anchored beneath the person's hand. The list contains various names written in different handwriting styles. The person's expression is contemplative, and they are adorned with a headpiece that includes both traditional elements and a piece of the American flag. In their hand, they holds a torch. The colors are varied, but mostly blue, orange, black purple and white.
A person holding a pigeon close to their chest with both hands. The person is depicted with blue and black tones against a textured, multicolored background.

column4: Courage! with us the people always go first
column7: A scene of two people in a wooden boat, with one person, who is larger pulling the other person, who looks frightened. The larger person is speaking, with a speech bubble that says, "Coragem!!! Com nós o povo sempre vai primeiro!!" (translates to "Courage!!! With us, the people always go first!!"). The other person, smaller and paited in brown skin color is in a defensive posture. The boat is on a greenish sea, which is populated with sharks emerging from the water. The sky in the background is gray. The mural is signed by "Paulo Ito 2018." Two characters in a wooden boat, facing imminent danger from large shark fins circling around them in a greenish sea.

column4: How about the rights? - you have the right to remain silent!
column7: A scene where a yellow path splits into two: one that ascends a mountain and another that goes to the right. On the path that ascends the mountain, several people are walking or running toward a sign that says "Employment". Along the way, some figures in suits and with bald heads are holding a whip. To the right, the path extends further, representing "the rights". A person on the main path asks, "MAS E OS DIREITOS?" which translates to "But what about the rights?" to which another responds with a speech bubble that says, "VOCÊ TEM O DIREITO DE FICAR CALADO!!" with translates to "You have the right to remain silent!!". The sky above is a mix of soft tones of blue and orange. The mural is signed by the artist.

A large glass bottle floating in the middle of an ocean. The bottle is tilted slightly, with a heart inside. The heart is painted in red, standing out against the cooler colors of the water and sky. The ocean waves are rendered in shades of purple and pink. Small boats are scattered across the water, painted in dark silhouettes. The sky above is filled with clouds in shades of orange, yellow, and purple. The color palette combines warm and cool tones, with purples, pinks, and oranges dominating the scene.

column4: Culture, ma'am? -no way! what will the neighbors think??
column7: A young person standing next to a car, holding a stack of books. They are wearing a hat, a t-shirt, and shorts. The person is speaking to a person inside the car, with a speech bubble that says, "Cultura, senhora?" ("Culture, ma'am?"). The person inside the car, whose hand is visible, responds with a speech bubble that says, "Eu hein! O que os vizinhos vão pensar??" ("no way! What will the neighbors think??"). The car's license plate reads "TPQ 123." The scene is painted on a gray brick wall, and the person and car are the primary figures in the mural. The artist's name, is written on the wall, along with the phrase "FORA TEMER."

column4: Thats how politician treat brasilian indians. Flooding their lands giving no choices
column7: A scene with several Indigenous people partially submerged in water, looking distressed. Above them, a large hand emerging from the top of the frame, is clad in a black business suit with a white shirt cuff. The hand holds a noose, painted in a dull grayish color, which dangles above the heads of the individuals. The background has a barren, leafless trees, which stand against the pale sky, suggesting a desolate environment. The overall color palette is muted and somber, with subtle pastels and earth tones. the sky has pale shades of blue, contrasting with tones of brown and orange of the skin tones. The water itself is a light greenish hue. The artist signature is visible on the right side of the artwork.

column4: (Aggressions that ruralists cause to the Brazilian environment)
column7: A figure resembling a businessperson, seated on a tree stump in a clear-cut forest. The individual is focused on a small booklet labeled "Plans," seemingly oblivious to the environmental devastation surrounding them. The color scheme features natural hues of green and brown for the grass and tree stumps, with a dusky sky. The character is colored with pink skin and a dark suit. (Note: Mural in protest against the environmental damage caused by agribusiness in Brazil. Depicts a suited person using the stump of a freshly cut tree as a toilet seat, highlighting the consequences of environmental exploitation).

column4: the great god money demands sacrifice!
column7: A person in a suit, standing with their hand on the shoulder of a young boy. The adult is pointing toward a dark, smoke-filled sky above a city skyline that is engulfed in flames and lightning. The expression on the boy's face suggests confusion or concern as they listens to the man. Above them, a caption reads, "O GRANDE DEUS DINHEIRO EXIGE SACRIFÍCIO!" (which translates to "The great god of money demands sacrifice!"). The colors are dark and ominous, with the contrast of the flames and lightning against the smoky, grey background.

Two people  interacting. On the left, a tall, skinny, shirtless person with a towel wrapped around their waist is offering a bowl to another figure. This person has a large hole in their abdomen, where their stomach would be, suggesting hunger. They stands shirtless, with a towel wrapped around their waist, holding out a bowl with both hands, as if they are begging or requesting something. On the right, a shorter, stockier person is seated on a small stool. They are also shirtless, with a stern expression on their face. their chest has a rough patch, almost as if something was torn out. They are holding a piece of paper or a placard in one hand, while their other hand is raised with a single finger pointing up, as if making a point. their expression and gesture imply authority. This person also has a void, but this one is located in their chest, right where their heart should be. This heart-shaped hole could symbolize emotional emptiness or a lack of compassion. The seated person is wearing blue sneakers, contrasting with their otherwise undressed state. The background is a rough, gray brick wall. The color palette is mostly muted, with occasional pops of color like the red noses on both figures and the blue shoes of the seated man.
A large green recycling symbol in green with three black ants crawling on and around it. The symbol is set against a pale wall.

Two cartoon-like characters are interacting with a television screen. On the left side of the image, there a figure resembling Pinocchio, with their iconic long nose extending into the TV screen. They are dressed in their attire with a green hat, pink bow tie, and blue shorts. On the right side, a young person with long brown hair and wearing a blue dress stands in front of the TV, looking up at the screen. The television displays the word "SUSTENTABILIDADE" (Portuguese for "Sustainability") along with an image of a small green plant or sprout. The background of the mural features a cityscape with industrial buildings and smoke rising from chimneys, suggesting pollution. The floor appears to be made of wooden planks, and there are green leaves extending into the scene from the right side.

A light bulb from which a spectrum of colorful, smoke-like trails flows out, each trail containing different symbols such as a peace sign, a musical note, and a heart. The text "IDEIA CERTA" (Correct Idea) is displayed around the bulb. A wide array of bright colors is used to fill the trails emanating from the light bulb, set against a pale blue background.

A group of three indigenous people in a canoe, seemingly on a sparse water source, while a large, bald figure (a man) is drinking the remaining water through a straw. The person appears to be draining the water source directly beneath the canoe. Earthy tones dominate the background, contrasting with the blue water and the pink hue of the large man.

A shirtless person standing on a pile of red and white life rings, lifting another life ring upwards. Above them, a sculpted figure dressed in a red shirt and white pants stands on a wooden block, looking down. The person below seems to be offering the life ring to the figure above, as if encouraging their to jump to safety. The colors are predominantly red, white, and earthy tones, emphasizing the contrast between the two figures and their actions.

Two hands forming a a heart symbol shape with their fingers against a blue and red background. The colors are a mix of flesh tones for the skin, deep blues for the clothing, and a bold red background that may be part of another element not fully visible in this segment of the mural.

A shirtless person smiling with a background consisting of geometric shapes. The colors are a mix of warm tones; the person is painted with natural skin tones, while the background features a vibrant mosaic of oranges, purples, blues, and yellows.

A partial, close-up of an eye of a person peering through a green foliage. The rest of the mural is a colorful geometric pattern. The colors include green for the leaves, flesh tones for the eye and skin, and a variety of bright colors such as yellow, pink, blue, and grey for the geometric shapes.

A panoramic composition blending nature and human elements. On the left side, there is a close-up of a person's face, painted with traditional indigenous patterns in shades of red and brown. In the center, there's lush green foliage, representing the natural environment. On the right side, the face of a jaguar emerges, with its piercing eyes and detailed fur in orange, black, and yellow. The artwork spans across a grassy hill. The colors are vivid and earthy.

column4: Svet kakav želiš / The World you want
column7: A mural spread across four columns. The leftmost section is an abstract composition made up of bold, overlapping shapes and colors. The palette includes reds, greens, blues, yellows, and blacks, forming a dynamic and energetic pattern. The second section features a person standing gracefully, dressed in a flowing garment adorned with natural elements like fish and plants. The background includes a bright yellow sun and a white dove. The third includes a white silhouette and plants, flowers, and dragonflies, with vibrant reds, greens, and blues dominating the palette. The rightmost section depicts a figure of a person in silhouette, rendered in dark tones with a subtle green tint. They holds a red book in their hand, standing next to a lighthouse in the background with a bright yellow ribbon that flows across the top of the panel. Poppies in red bloom at their feet.
A stylized scene with birds and a variety of flowers, set against a backdrop of clouds and foliage. The colors are bright with a palette that includes yellow, red, purple, blue, and green.

A large hand detailed in natural skin tones is prominently depicted, with the fingers gently pinching a needle in a large spherical object resembling a bubble. Inside this sphere, clouds of smoke come from the vertical black industrial chimes. The background of the mural is covered in green foliage and leaves, with a dense, natural pattern that contrasts with the hand and the sphere. There is also a tag on the bottom left corner of the mural.

column3: Mona Carón (Artist's assistant: Lisa Ruth Elliott)
column7: A large, colorful depiction of various vegetables, such as broccoli, carrots, and radishes, growing amidst a deep blue background. These vegetables are portrayed as oversized, with vibrant green leaves that stretch across the mural. Interwoven with the imagery of the vegetables is a large, flowing scroll that winds through the scene. This scroll contains detailed illustrations of a town. The color palette is earthy, with greens and browns for the plants, and a variety of other colors included within the scenes depicted on the ribbon. (Note: Contrasts two parts of 24th Street in San Francisco: the calm, sheltered Noe Valley neighborhood and the vibrant, complex Mission District. It features giant vegetables linked to the local farmers market and captures everyday life in Noe Valley, with neighbors enjoying coffee. In contrast, the Mission District section portrays street performances, demonstrations, and the diverse lives of working-class families, reflecting the area's rich cultural diversity).

A whimsical scene on a large brick wall, featuring a swirling ribbon-like structure that spirals through the air. The ribbon contains various images, including a landscape with green fields, a church, and what appears to be a scene from a theater or a festive gathering. At the top of the mural, a white bird, possibly a dove, flies above the ribbon. Below, two figures are depicted, one seems a clown holding onto the ribbon and being lifted into the air, while the other seems to be a child reaching out towards it. The colors in the mural are vibrant, with the ribbon and the human figures standing out against the muted tones of the brick wall. (On the artist's website, it is noted that the mural honors the renowned Swiss Clown Dimitri, their family of performers and musicians, and the Dimitri School of Physical Theater. Located on the southern wall facing the Parco Del Clown in Verscio, Switzerland, the mural depicts Dimitri balancing an elephant, which holds a ribbon featuring a detailed painting of the mural's location. This includes the artists associated with the school, reflecting the vibrant local artistic community.)

A flowing ribbon or band that twists through the composition, revealing different scenes and landscapes within its folds. Warm tones of the ribbon and architectural elements, and natural greens, blues, and yellows of the landscapes and flora. (Note: The mural's center highlights its geographic location on the Mission Trail between the San Jose and Dolores missions. It contrasts a vibrant, modern California landscape with historic red and gold tones, using a native wildflower to bridge past and present. The mural ends with a red-tailed hawk feather symbolizing the fading history of El Camino Real).

A person's face and hands emerging from a vivid blue background with dolphins.The dominant colors are shades of blue, suggesting water and ocean, with the skin tones of the woman. (Note: Created as part of a United Nations project, the mural is divided into sections, serving as an invitation to learn about the natural oceanic treasures in Playas of Rosarito. It emphasizes the importance of education in fostering care, respect, and love for the ocean while advocating for policies to keep the ocean clean, reduce plastic use, and properly treat wastewater).

On the left side, a figure looks upward with a sense of despair or longing, as dark, ominous clouds swirl above, filled with birds that appear to be crows. Below, a large, fallen figure lies on the ground, their body stretched out across the canvas. Smaller figures surround the fallen person, seemingly mourning. The background on the right side transitions into shades of gray, where multiple faces emerge from the clouds, their expressions contorted in anguish or shouting. The overall color palette is dominated by warm hues of orange, red, and yellow on the left, transitioning into darker, cooler tones of gray and black on the right.

column3: Adry del Rocío & Carlos Alberto GH
column4: Home is where the heart is / Hogar es donde está tu corazón
column7: An individual, possibly indigenous, adorned with a headdress and surrounded by a multitude of birds in various states of flight. The colors are vivid and varied. (Note: The 3D mural titled "Home is where the heart is" is dedicated to all those who have had to leave their place of origin).
column9:
Adry del Rocío & 
Carlos Alberto GH

column7: A person surrounded by a variety of marine animals, creating a vivid tapestry of ocean life that seems to emerge from the individual. The individual is in a serene expression, with hands extended, as if to show a nurturing gesture towards the sea creatures that envelop them. The colors are rich with a dominance of blues and purples, and warmer tones of the person's skin. (The 3D mural titled "Renaissance" invites reflection on the direction we must take as individuals and as humanity. It highlights the fragility of life by depicting creatures that are either extinct or at high risk of extinction, emphasizing the urgency of taking action. The mural highlights a variety of endangered and extinct species, such as the extinct Giant Sea Turtle (Archelon), endangered Axolotl (Ambystoma mexicanum), the extinct Chinese River Dolphin (Lipotes vexillifer), endangered Humphead Wrasse (Cheilinus undulatus), extinct Giant Ammonite, endangered Manatee (Trichechus), critically endangered Vaquita Porpoise (Phocoena sinus), extinct Japanese Sea Lion (Zalophus japonicus), and extinct Trilobites. The artwork serves as a reminder of the importance of both small and large actions to protect the delicate balance of life on Earth).

column4: If nothing can save us from dead, at least love can save us from life
column7: A child holds a stylized bird that appears to blend into or emerge from a heart shape. The bird's colors features hues of blue and green. Along with the bird and heart, there appears to be a fish. The child is also holding something in their hand, an object that signifies a particular theme or message the artist wants to convey.

An elderly person, seated on the ground with their legs crossed. their body is bare, with detailed musculature and the textures of their aged skin. their head is tilted upward, their long gray hair and beard flowing back, giving a sense of movement or divine inspiration. One arm is raised toward the sky, with the hand open in a gesture that suggests a plea or a prayer. their other arm, slightly bent, rests on their lap. Behind the person, there are red drapery-like elements. The figure is bathed in a warm light that gives the scene a spiritual or transcendental atmosphere. The overall color palette has warm hues of red, yellow, and orange, with cooler tones in the shadows.

Painting on a brick pavement, depicting a person with a glowing halo around their head. They gazes directly at the viewer, with their hands outstretched as if asking something or reaching out. Surrounding their are images of people in various expressions and gestures, some appearing distressed or anguished. Red petals are scattered throughout the scene, adding a contrast to the predominantly warm tones of the mural. The artist's signature is visible in the bottom right corner.

A person wrapped in a flowing white veil. They holds a human heart in their hands, with vibrant red flowers surrounding them. The scene is set on what appears to be a pavement, creating an illusion of the figure emerging from the ground. Scattered petals are displayed. The artist's signature is visible in the bottom left corner. Colors: soft whites, grays of the veil, reds of the flowers and heart. (Note: The 3D street painting titled "We are not three" is dedicated to the memory of all Mexicans who have disappeared and lost their lives. It serves as a tribute, ensuring that they are not forgotten).

Two children engaged in an adventure. One child (a boy) is wearing blue pajamas adorned with stars, holds a wooden sword aloft and wears a paper sailor hat, embodying a sense of playful courage. The other child (a girl) dressed in a bright yellow coat with long flowing red hair, appears to be guiding their journey with a shepherd's staff. The children are seated in a colorful, oversized umbrella that seems to be floating among the clouds. The background features a deep blue circular sky filled with yellow stars, a crescent moon, and additional playful details like pink and purple stars. The mural is painted on a brick wall. The artist's signature is visible in the bottom left corner.
A child with blue hair engaging with a pink toy or imaginary friend, with a glowing heart between them. Colors: bright blue and pink standing out against the dark backdrop.
The phrase "NO WAR" is overlaid on a collection of faces and figures with diverse individuals. The colors are vibrant, with a mix of blues and yellows dominating the palette.

A young person lying down and reading a book, with a bright pink dress and a pattern of stars on their clothing. The color scheme features a combination of bold and pastel colors, with the bright yellows and rays.

A person sitting with a large pink hippopotamus under a starry sky, accompanied by a small orange creature, possibly a bird or a fantastical animal. Colors: pink of the hippopotamus, orange of the small creature, purple of the night sky and the yellow stars.

The mural features two children, one black and one white, alongside the words "LOVE MATTERS." They seem to be interacting warmly, with one child holding a heart symbol, likely to convey a message of unity and friendship across racial lines.

1) This image celebrates diversity and friendship, with each child representing racial inclusivity and the universal nature of love.

2) The artwork reflects SDG 10: Reduced Inequalities, focusing on the reduction of inequality within and among countries, promoting the social, economic, and political inclusion of all, irrespective of race.

3) The art style is playful and illustrative, employing a child-like simplicity to express a powerful and inclusive message.

4) The colors are bold and contrasting, with the white and black skin tones of the children providing visual symbolism of racial diversity and harmony.

5) The dominant figures are the two children, and the heart symbol they interact with is a central visual element that ties the composition together.

6) Keywords might include "diversity," "racial harmony," "children," "love," and "equality."

7) The mural's meaning could be interpreted as a call for unity and love across racial divides, emphasizing the innocence of children as a model for society.

8) The valence tone is decidedly positive, as it promotes a message of hope, love, and the importance of overcoming racial barriers to achieve a more inclusive and equal world.

A person and two children, all painted in shades of brown, with elongated and stylized features. A real tree in front of the mural seems to blend into the scene, partially obscuring the figures. The person is wearing a bright yellow garment adorned with green floral patterns against the earthy tones of their skin and the background. The children are shown engaging with the person, possibly in play, with one child partially submerged in what appears to be water, as suggested by the blue background. The backdrop includes natural elements, with the blue representing water and leaves from a tree painted in green at the top left corner.

A person holding a bird in their hands against a backdrop that includes a heart shape. The setting and attire suggest a connection to African culture. The color palette is composed of natural, muted tones like browns, ochres, and tans, with the heart rendered in a rust-like color.

A figure, likely a person, with an intricate hairstyle or headpiece, which merges with the trees and leaves painted around them. The color palette includes earthy tones for the figure and the trees, with vibrant greens for the leaves.

Two large profiles of people facing each other, both with braided hair. An external hand is depicted on the left side of the mural, appearing to braid or adjust the hair of the person on the left. The person on the right has long braids that hang down. The background features bright orange and peach tones, creating a vibrant contrast with the sand-like color of the people's faces. A door and a window are integrated into the mural, positioned between the two people. The artist's name is visible on the right side of the mural.
A sea turtle, occupying the corner of a building, giving the illusion that the creature is swimming around the structure. The color palette has blues and greens with yellow and white highlights.

column4: The Old person and the Sea
column7: An elderly person, set against an abstract background with splashes of paint and vivid colors. The color palette includes a mix of earthy tones in the person's features, while the background has yellows and greens.

A series of panels, one displaying a close-up of hands working with a tool, and another showing a focused face of a person, presumably a worker or craftsperson, engaged in physical labor. The color palette is subdued, relying on a monochromatic scheme with shades of brown and beige.
Two side-by-side portraits displaying two different expressions. The color palette is warm, dominated by earthy tones with accents of blue.

A profile of a person (possibly a woman) with a expression representing determination. The individual has short, curly hair that is colored in shades of blue, wearing a large, beaded necklace in red and orange hues that wraps around the neck and shoulders. The background features a dynamic pattern of blue and red shapes, with circles and curves. The mural is painted on a brick wall. The artist's signature is visible on the right side of the mural.

In the center, a bird, possibly a roadrunner, is perched on the rim of an overturned, colorful toilet. Two potted plants sit on top of the toilet. One pot is blue, while the other is green. The plants have lush green leaves, and their vines and stems drape over the sides. The backdrop consists of warm hues, including shades of pink, orange, and purple, giving a soft, sunset-like atmosphere to the scene. Green foliage and grass grow around the base of the toilet, merging the environment with the unnatural placement of the toilet and pots.

Two figures seated on a couch; the one on the left - a person - is holding a camera and appears to be taking a selfie, while the figure on the right has their face obscured by a pillow. The color palette used blue and warm tones. (Note: Part of the series called "Antithesis of Urbanization," the work highlights the idea that technology, like the phone, should be used to shorten distances rather than to prolong conversations, as highlighted by the artist).

column4: Rèv Rive Nan Fè Nwa / Dreams Happen in the Dark
column7: The upper part of the mural showcases abstract shapes that resemble large, dark leaves or feathers with blue and red accents. These shapes fan out from the center, where a pair of eyes, barely visible, appears to be closed. Below the abstract design, a black and white photo-realistic depiction shows a group of people in a dimly lit space. This section is contrasted by the zigzag patterns in purple, blue, and green on either side, which seem to flow into the central image. At the bottom of the mural, there is a phrase in white text that reads "RÈV RIVE NAN FÈ NWA," which is Creole for "Dreams come in darkness."

A portrayal of of Martin Luther King Jr., along with a raised fist. Accompanying the visuals are phrases "The time is always right to do what is right" and "The time is always... right to do what is right...", which are attributed to King. The colors are muted, with sepia tones for the figure against the red brick background, while the fist and text incorporate pastel shades.

Two distinct sections: The left side shows the profile of a person, with dark skin in shades of deep blue. The person appears to be either kissing or blowing towards the petals of a large sunflower, which are yellow with tips fading into pinkish-red. The right side depicts a muscular figure from the waist up, flexing their right arm. The background behind their features a pattern of intersecting lines in red and yellow, forming a geometric design. The person’s skin is rendered in brown tones.

Mural painted on the corner of a building, using the structure to create the visual effect. The scene features two large hands, each extending from either side of the building. The hands appear to be grasping a natural landscape that spans across both walls. The landscape depicted includes snow-capped mountains in the center, with rocky, arid terrain on the lower parts of the mural. Above the mountainous landscape, the sky is represented with geometric in various shades of red, orange, blue, and purple.

A person's head and shoulders emerging a background in red and orange. This scene represents the aftermath of violence in Chicago, where confrontations led to riots, fires, and social disruption. (Note: A tribute to Eugene Williams and the Red Summer, a tragic event in history (1919), when a Black person was unjustly arrested after a confrontation on the "Black side" of a Chicago beach. The incident sparked widespread violence, leading to weeks of riots, shootings, and arson, leaving thousands homeless. The piece serves as a catalyst for positive change in the future).
Three garage doors of the Las Vegas Fire Department, Station 103, each adorned with a unique piece of art. Each door features a silhouette against a background of flames and smoke.
A group of individuals with distressed expressions, reaching out for help, against a dark, tumultuous water background. They are wearing orange life vests associated with maritime safety.

Two figures with air bubbles around them, which could represent the excavation of history and the unearthing of past civilizations, likened to the process of mining. Title "Archaeology is Mining for Knowledge".

A profile of a person in blue tones, with their hair and features merging with a floral element, which in turn transitions into a mountainous landscape. This integration of huperson, flora, and the natural environment. Use of blue hues throughout the image and red to the flower. (Note: "Portrait of a Mother" features a person in profile in blue, with elements like Mount Whitney, sagebrush, and a carnation. The person, nurturing their flock of sheep, symbolizes care and nature. The carnation, symbolizing the intricate workings of the brain, ties in with the mural’s ceremonial and decorative purpose).

Homage to the "Candy Bomber," a term given to U.S. pilot Gail Halvorsen, who dropped candy attached to parachutes to children during the Berlin Airlift after World War II. Shows an older person in profile, laughing or smiling, with a pilot's cap, evoking the joyful spirit of Halvorsen. In the background, a stylized representation of an airplane dropping candy can be seen, with hands reaching upwards to catch the falling treats.

A series of hands holding various paintings, with the larger mural itself spread across multiple surfaces. Each painting within the mural depicts a different scene: Leftmost Panel: A person holds a blue flag with a yellow star and a circular emblem, which is likely the Nevada state flag. Second Panel: A person holds a painting of a kingfisher bird perched on a rock near a body of water. The background showcases a sunset over a landscape with mountains and water. Third Panel: A set of hands displays a painting featuring a dramatic sunset with dark clouds over a body of water, creating a striking contrast of colors. Rightmost Panel: A person holding a painting of two silhouetted animals (possibly bighorn sheep) against a night sky. A shooting star or comet streaks across the sky in this scene. The colors range from the blues and yellows of the flag to the vibrant hues of sunsets and the dark tones of a nighttime scene.

A figure, possibly a girl, seemingly in a state of distress or contemplation, with their hand on their forehead looking upward. Adjacent to the figure are what appear to be wings or feathered elements.

A monochromatic blue depiction of a young person in profile. The person is dressed in a traditional-looking dress, and they are carrying a baby in a sling on their back, suggesting a maternal or caretaker role despite their young age. The child in the sling is partially visible. The girl's has one hand raised to their mouth. The entire figure is rendered in various shades of blue. The background is a plain, pale color.

A close-up depiction of a hand reaching out towards the viewer, set against a backdrop that includes a representation of a blue house. The image of the house appears somewhat distant or miniature in comparison to the scale of the hand. (Note: A young child holding a model of a low-income home provided by the Reno Housing Authority, symbolizing the importance of affordable housing for families in need).

A person in the foreground with one hand framing their face and the second raising a fist. Behind their is a backdrop featuring abstract shapes, flowers. On the right side, there is a depiction of three figures standing together, set against a purple backdrop with the number 200 and an electric meter. The color palette has purples, oranges, and greens.
Two individuals in a close and intimate embrace. The use of a monochromatic scheme focuses the viewer on the subjects' interlocked forms and expressions.

A series of distinct panels, each portraying a different subject. From left to right, there's a leopard with a fierce expression, a person playing with a flute, a smiling individual adorned with a colorful headwrap, and a person playing the trumpet, with music and celebration implied by the text "Carnaval de Puebla".

A figure lying back in the water with reflections on the water's surface in a grayscale palette. (Note: A surreal interpretation of reality, divided by an almost imperceptible line that vanishes as we submerge or emerge within our own being).

A person looking upwards with an expression of hope, framed by hands that are gently cupped and facing upward as well. The background transitions from warm reds and oranges to cool blues. The person depicted in the mural appears to be Black. their features, as well as the styling of their hair, suggest that they are of African descent. The artist has chosen to render their image in grayscale.

Three individuals, likely women, in grayscale against a colorful background. The individuals are adorned with traditional clothing and accessories, which, along with their features, suggest they may represent a specific cultural or ethnic group. The colors of their garments contrast with the monochrome of their faces.

A figure aiming a rifle with a scope with colored birds in flight around the barrel, creating a contrast between the themes of violence and nature. Use of grayscale for the figure and the weapon focuses the viewer's attention on the action and the facial expression, while the birds add a jarring element of beauty and life.

Central portrait of an elderly woman. their face is rendered in black and white, and they are smiling with one hand resting on their cheek. The background around the portrait is dominated by a bright blue color and it includes various fantastical and colorful elements. On the left, there is an abstract sun-like face with rays extending outward, painted in a mix of yellow, orange, and blue. Nearby, a small bird with white wings is depicted mid-flight, approaching the woman’s face. On the right side, another abstract face in shades of blue, surrounded by intricate designs and patterns. Red and white floral and leafy patterns extend across the lower portion of the mural. The mural is bordered at the top and bottom by a red stripe.

column4: The Wall of the Invisible / El muro de los invisibles
column7: A close-up, grayscale portrait of an elderly person, with highly detailed facial features. Use of grayscale.

A close-up of an elderly individual's hands held in a gesture that may suggest prayer. The details of the wrinkles and the texture of the skin are rendered in grayscale. (Note: "Urban Prayers" represent souls crying out in abandonment and despair, pleading with life for justice, peace, and love).

Monochromatic, highly detailed portrait of an elderly person, smiling broadly and holding their hands to their cheeks. The background includes colorful illustrations of birds and abstract designs that resemble musical notes or DNA strands.
A child wearing pilot goggles and a helmet. Above the child is a hand holding a paper airplane.

An anthropomorphic character, a mouse dressed in sailor attire, sitting on a paper plane as it glides through the air. The backdrop features a pastoral scene with trees and flying birds bathed hues of a sunset or sunrise.
An anthropomorphic frog riding a bicycle, with a large bird, possibly a heron or a stork, in flight next to it. The sun in the background with a landscape of trees and flowers.

Four pineapples lined up side by side at the bottom of the image. Above the pineapples, in bold, the word "Juicy" written in a gradient of yellow and white. Below the phrase "Daily Fresh!" is written in white. The background is a mix of blue and teal tones, which complements the green leaves of the pineapples. At the bottom, the mural is signed with "MOPE * 2020..." in white graffiti-style text.

The character Popeye is holding cans of spinach. The mural uses bold lettering, with the character shown in a joyful and triumphant pose, reminiscent of the cartoon's themes of gaining strength from eating spinach.

A shirtless person wearing a green cap with the word "Opfa" written. They are setting up a trap, using a cardboard box labeled "94" as the trap mechanism. The box is propped up by a stick tied to a string that the person is holding. Inside the trap, there is a piece of yellow cheese. Several white mice are scattered around the scene—some are on the person's arm, one is perched on their shoulder, while others are near the trap. The background is a plain wall with minimal color of blue and white.

Large glass bottles float in the ocean, each bottle containing different scenes. The six bottles are partially submerged in the water, with the contents visible through the clear glass. The scenes inside the bottles include marine life like dolphins and fish, a diver, and two children sitting together. The water is painted in varying shades of blue and teal, with additional fish swimming outside the bottles in the open sea. The sky above transitions from warm tones of orange and pink at the horizon to darker shades higher up, where clouds are scattered across the sky. Birds are also seen flying in the sky.

A figure, likely a teenager or young person, sitting with their knees drawn up to their chest, facing sideways. The figure is painted in shades of gray and black, which blend into the shadows surrounding them. The background features a rough outline in a rusty orange or brown color. The wall behind the mural is painted white. (Note: The mural highlights the harsh reality of homelessness, drawing a parallel between childhood games of building cardboard forts and the grim situation of living in a cardboard box on the streets. The mural serves as a call to give back to the homeless, encouraging everyone to embrace the spirit of helping those in need).

A young boy, painted in grayscale, touching a globe depicted with bright colors—green for the landmasses and blue for the oceans. The globe has a bandage around it, as if it has been wounded and is in need of healing, with red drops below, suggesting blood. The boy's pose, facing away from the viewer, gives the impression that they are concerned or trying to help the Earth in some way. The scene is framed within a recessed area, and the ground in front of the mural has some objects, including a bright orange book and loose papers.

Three people of different ethnicities standing side by side, each with their backs to the viewer. Their torsos are bare, and the phrase "ALL LIVES MATTER" is written across their backs, with each word on a different person's back. They are wrapped in white fabric from the waist down. The colors are relatively muted, with the brown background providing contrast to the white fabric and the skin tones of the women, which range from dark to light. The red text stands out against the skin tones and background.

A child crouching on the ground holding a teddy bear, with a menacing, shadowy adult figure looming over them. The background is a gradient from dark at the top to lighter near the bottom. There's text on the right side saying "Stop Child Abuse" and "Pin the ribbon on the ass" with blue ribbons displayed beneath.

Two indigenous figures on either side, one standing and one kneeling, both poised with bows and arrows. Between them is a young tree, flanked by two large posts labeled "NATURE PRESERVATION BOUNDARY." 4) The color scheme consists of earth tones for the human figures and tree, with contrasting bright orange for the boundary markers, and a muted background that does not detract from the main subjects.

A series of figures painted on a wooden fence, each progressively standing on the shoulders of the one before to spray paint a symbol that resembles a fist inside a gender symbol on the wall. The first figure on the left is crouched down, holding a stencil, and the subsequent figures are using the stencil to create the symbol. The color scheme is mostly grayscale for the figures, which stand in stark contrast to the bright pink of the gender symbol.

column4: ¡Majer tu voz es fuerte!  / “Women; , your voice is strong”
column7: Back view of a person with long, flowing hair. The person is partially draped in a cloth that wraps around their shoulders and waist, leaving their back exposed. Across their back, the words "MUJER, TÚ ERES FUERTE" are written in blue letters (translating to "person, you are strong" in English). The color palette is muted, with shades of gray and white dominating the scene, while the text in blue.

The mural features a small child, depicted in grayscale, standing against an orange brick wall. The child holds a teddy bear in one hand and appears to be looking up at a lineup of black, stencil-style assault rifles on a white background. The rifles are stacked vertically, and each one is labeled with the name of a different school where a shooting has occurred: ROB ELEMENTARY (topmost rifle), STONE person DOUGLAS, SANDY HOOK, COLUMBINE HIGH (bottom rifle).

A group of people covered in blue burqas, with only their eyes visible through the narrow slits in the fabric. The focal point of the image is a person at the center, whose face is slightly more revealed than the others, allowing their eyes and eyebrows to be seen. their eyes are intensely expressive. The mural is painted on a metal surface. The dominant color is a deep blue, contrasted by the lighter tones used to highlight the folds of the fabric, and the pale skin of the visible face.

The world map on a melting candle, with the continents dripping down like wax. A flame burns brightly at the top of the candle. The color scheme is predominantly blue, representing the oceans on the world map, with the continents in brown. The yellow and orange of the flame provide a contrast to the cool blue tones of the earth. (Note: Created on Earth Day to make a statement about the Earth's condition. The candle is burning down the planet, symbolizing the planet's ongoing deterioration).

A monochromatic mural depicting several individuals behind bars. The text "HUMANS ARE NOT FOR SALE" is displayed above. The figures appear distressed, with their hands pressed against the bars, emphasizing a sense of captivity and longing for freedom. Barcodes below the figures. (Note: Inspired by the alarming rise in child and human sex trafficking within the US, the artist highlights the horrifying reality of exploiting and selling vulnerable children, portraying it as the ultimate loss of freedom and humanity).

Two distinct panels. On the left side, there are two hands forming a heart shape, with various protest signs and messages filling the background. These signs display phrases such as "For Breonna and George," "Your fight is our fight," "End police brutality," "Defund white supremacy," and "Vote for change". The heart shape created by the hands reveals a reflective surface or a mirror. On the right side, a portrait of a Black person with a calm yet determined expression. their face is surrounded by similar protest messages, including "BLM" (Black Lives Matter), "We are sacred," "Stop killing us," and "Protect Black women". The person's face is painted in grayscale, . their eyes seem to be gazing directly at the viewer. The dominant colors in the mural are shades of gray and black, with red used to highlight certain words. The artist's signature is visible in the bottom right corner of the right panel.

Six human figures climbing and hanging onto two large horizontal yellow bars set against a deep blue background. The figures are rendered in a monochromatic grayscale, contrasting with the bright yellow of the bars. The bars appear to be suspended by ropes. One figure appears to be pulling another up, while another figure is hanging onto the bar. The yellow bar in the center has a section where the paint appears to be melting or dripping, with multicolored paint (red, green, yellow, and blue) flowing downward. The mural is signed in the upper right corner, indicating the artist. (Note: "Time to Raise the Bar" emphasizes the need for collective action to build equality, peace, and harmony among ourselves. The message is that we, as individuals, hold the power to create change—not the government or anyone else. To achieve this, we must stop fighting each other and start listening with compassion).

column4: WE MUST TEACH OUR CHILDREN TO RESPECT THE LAND
column7: An adult figure leading a child by the hand, both rendered in a monochrome palette. Above them is the word "WAR" in yellow. To the right is a message in red stating, "We must teach our children to respect the land". The color scheme is muted with the figures in grayscale against the off-white background.

Numerous hands reaching toward the center of the composition. The hands vary in size and tone. Most of the hands appear to be in shades of brown, with a few hands in lighter tones, all blending seamlessly into the darker background. One prominent hand in the lower section of the mural is painted in white, and it seems to be holding something golden, resembling a coin or a symbol of value. This hand stands out sharply against the other hands and the background. The mural is signed by the artist in the lower right corner.

A child with closed eyes and a somber expression, holding a pencil and drawing on their chest. From the back of the child, two large wings made up of multiple colorful flags from around the world extend outward. The color scheme is predominantly grayscale for the child, contrasted with the colors of the flags.

Fusion of a person's face and a jaguar, with the animal's features superimposed on the person's face. The background is filled with abstract shapes and large, colorful flowers that frame the central figures.

An person’s face in profile, eyes closed. The face is framed by hands. The background is filled with a kaleidoscope of abstract, geometric shapes in a variety of colors that add contrast to the earthy tones of the hands and face.
A person with a crown of flowers. The individual's hands are forward, with one hand releasing an array of butterflies. The other hand has flames rising from the fingertips . The background is green.
A close-up of a gorilla's face, expressing emotion with the mouth open. The gorilla is set against a backdrop of abstract shapes and flames that seem to emanate from the creature.

A child's face flanked by hands painted with rainbow colors. The child's expression is of joy, and the colorful hands appear to be raised in play. Behind the child, abstract shapes and designs. The color scheme is varied, with the hands displaying a full spectrum of colors; the child has more naturally toned face.

A person with closed eyes, holding the hands near the face as if gently blowing or cupping something. The person's face and hands are rendered in warm colors, including shades of orange, yellow, and pink. Surrounding the person are vibrant, large green leaves and blue flowers with touches of pink and purple. The background is a gradient of bright orange and yellow. The artist's tag appears in white on the top right corner of the mural.

An elderly person with long white hair, holding a bowl filled with soil and a young plant. Surrounding their are various fruits and vegetables, including corn, avocado, tomatoes, and carrots, against a colorful background. Colors: Mix of bright and earthy colors, including shades of green, yellow, orange, red, and blue.

Three interlocked hands of different colors and races (symbolizing unity and collaboration). Surrounding the hands are colorful flowers. Bright and varied colors, including shades of yellow, orange, purple, blue, green, and pink.

An elderly person, likely of indigenous descent, wearing traditional attire and a colorful headdress. The person is adorned with a large earring and set against a background of abstract, colorful shapes and elements of nature. A broad spectrum of bright colors, including yellows, greens, blues, reds, and purples.

Three children of different ethnic backgrounds, all smiling. They are surrounded by large flowers and green foliage, which frame their faces against a colorful background. A wide range of bright colors, including shades of orange, green, purple, blue, and pink.

Two elderly people interacting intimately. One person is playfully squinting with a surprised expression, while the other person is kissing the other cheek. The mural is monochromatic with pink accents and graffiti letter elements.

A person with their eyes closed, embracing the Earth, which is partly aflame. their hair is adorned with flowers and green leaves. The background is filled with colorful geometric shapes and patterns. A wide range of bright colors, including shades of blue, green, purple, pink, orange, and yellow.

A group of children and a few adults gathered around, focused on an object one of the children is holding. Colors: Muted color palette, with shades of blue, gray, brown, and black. (Note: Artist's Instagram post explains that the mural was inspired by the Museu de Lisboa's collection to reflect the history and residents of the local neighborhood. They chose to modernize "The Reading," incorporating local children who participate in an afterschool program run by volunteer women in the community. These women dedicate their time to assisting children with their challenges and promoting an atmosphere of acceptance and inclusion).

An elderly person sitting and looking thoughtfully to the side. They are surrounded by newspapers and photographs, which seem to document historical events and personal memories. The backdrop is filled with large, detailed newspaper clippings. Colors: Muted color palette, primarily consisting of shades of brown, beige, and gray.

A multi-story building with various people on its balconies and staircases. The individuals are engaged in different activities, such as talking, leaning on railings, or interacting with each other. The scene depicts the communal life, showing social interactions in a shared living space. Colors: Muted colors with shades of gray, brown, green, and blue. (Note: Aims to capture everyday life and the interactions that occur in the stairwells of local buildings, which featured locals who consented to be photographed, reflecting the unique narrative of the neighborhood).

A group of elderly people sitting together outdoors, engaged in knitting or similar handiwork. The scene is monochromatic, emphasizing the figures against a textured background of stone steps and walls.

A group of people from the early 20th century, dressed in period attire, including cloche hats and fur-collared coats. They are gathered together, engaged in conversation, with a background that suggests they are in a public or social setting, such as a race track or a fairground, indicated by the fencing and the crowd in the background. Colors: Muted, earthy tones such as browns, beiges, and grays, with some pastel accents in the women’s clothing.

column4: The Chorus Women;  of “Murder in the Cathedral”
column7: Multiple women, depicted in a monochromatic color scheme. The people are shown wearing headscarves and looking determined or thoughtful, suggesting a sense of resilience and solidarity. The expressions on their faces reflect a range of emotions, adding depth and complexity to the artwork.

People working together, possibly in a workshop or factory setting. The people are engaged in what appears to be a craft or manufacturing activity, involving flowers or similar items. The scene is rendered in a monochromatic color scheme.

An orangutan holding a baby orangutan, with the larger orangutan raising its arm with a fist. The artwork is textured and three-dimensional, incorporating various materials and objects, giving it a unique, tactile appearance.

A sea turtle crafted using various pieces of discarded plastic and other materials, creating a textured and three-dimensional effect. The turtle is set against a background of blue and green hues, mimicking the ocean.

A ram with large, curved horns. The ram is depicted in a mixed-media style, with one half of the artwork made from a variety of discarded materials, including colorful plastic pieces, electronic parts, and metal objects. The other half is painted realistically, showcasing the natural texture and color of the ram's fur and horns.

A colorful owl constructed from various pieces of discarded plastic and other materials. The owl’s large eyes and detailed feathers are created using a mix of bright, vibrant colors and textures. The use of recycled materials gives the artwork a three-dimensional effect.
A mother bear with two cubs, created using various pieces of discarded materials, giving it a textured and three-dimensional appearance.
Two pelicans created using various pieces of discarded materials, giving them a textured and three-dimensional appearance. The birds are set against a blue and white background.

Two monkeys, a mother and their baby, created using various pieces of discarded materials. The monkeys are portrayed in an embrace. The use of recycled materials gives the artwork a textured and three-dimensional appearance.

A large moose and its calf, created using various pieces of discarded materials. The mural uses shades of brown, beige, and gray, reflecting the natural colors of moose. The use of recycled materials adds varied textures.

A seal created using various pieces of discarded materials, giving it a textured and three-dimensional appearance. The seal is shown in a seated position with expressive eyes. Colors: shades of gray and black to depict the seal; recycled materials with varied colors such as blue, green, yellow, purple, and red.

Two birds made from various pieces of discarded materials. The birds are surrounded by colorful plastic debris. The left side features a group of multi-colored birds, while the right side shows a larger bird in a more monochromatic palette, set against a red and white background.

A turtle created using various pieces of discarded materials, particularly colorful plastic debris. The turtle is shown in a naturalistic pose, with its shell and body composed of an array of vibrant, repurposed objects.

A bear created using various pieces of discarded materials. The bear is portrayed in a realistic manner, with detailed features that capture its expression and form. The background features a building facade with windows and the phrase "Before I die..." partially visible.

A young person with a determined expression, pointing upwards with their right hand. They are draped in a colorful scarf with stripes of red, yellow, and white. The background includes a circular halo-like element and a purple sky with clouds.

Two separate portraits of African American individuals. The left portrait features a person with a pink flower in their hair, facing left, with the word "BLACK" written above them. The right portrait shows a person in profile, facing right, with the words "LIVES MATTER" written beside them. The center panel is not part of the artwork and contains text unrelated to the portraits.

A person and a child with their heads partially transformed into landscapes. The person's head resembles a lush mountain with trees, while the child's head has a smaller mountain peak. Two birds, possibly herons, are depicted interacting with the landscape elements. Use of natural colors, including shades of green, blue, and brown. The sky is depicted in a bright blue with white clouds.

A pair of large blue hands sculpting a pot that resembles a sleeping baby’s face. The scene is set against a light blue sky with some clouds. The bottom of the mural includes a green landscape with a small sprout emerging from the ground. The mural uses shades of blue, green, and brown. The baby’s face is depicted in natural earth tones.

A central figure wearing a spacesuit, holding a scale of justice in one hand. Below, a green-hued person is cradling a child, surrounded by large leaves and plants. There is a prominent red ribbon tied in a bow at the bottom right. The background includes clouds and vegetation. The spacesuit and scales of justice are depicted in shades of white and gray, the protective figure and child are in green, the plants in green and brown, and the ribbon in bright red. The background includes blue sky and clouds.

A human figure with a bird's head, cradling a baby close to its chest. The bird-headed figure is shown in a protective and nurturing pose, with its beak open as if calling out.The mural uses shades of earthy tones, such as browns and tans, along with highlights of white and red.

Multiple fish heads are intertwined with a human face, creating a hybrid figure. The human face is looking to the left, and the fish heads are arranged around it, all with open mouths. An arm extends from the figure, with a hand reaching out. Above the scene is a small crown object. The background is a light green color, with a circular orange element behind the human face.

A figure with a yellow house for a head, crawling on the ground. The figure's body is human-like but elongated. The word "Ver" is displayed in large letters in the background, and the word "Precise" is written on the figure's side. The background is a neutral, textured wall, which contrasts with the detailed depiction of the figure. Primarily uses shades of brown and beige for the figure and background, with the house on the figure's head depicted in bright yellow.

Two figures with yellow houses on their back, depicted in crouching and reaching postures. Both figures are nude and appear elongated, with one figure extending an arm toward the other. The word "Ver de" is partially visible in large green letters on the background. The background is a white wall.

An elderly person wearing glasses and a white blouse with colorful stripes on the sleeves. They are holding an open book, looking up with an expression of pride or contemplation. The word "Viva" is written in large, bold red letters across the background, dominating the scene. The book they holds has the text "Maria Vilani professora, filósofa, escritora, mãe, e avó" (Maria Vilani teacher, philosopher, writer, mother, and grandmother).

A young person drinking from a can. The can features the word "das" prominently, while the text "Justiça" (Justice) is written across the boy's face, and "Vi" is written to the right of their head. The person is wearing a yellow shirt and is looking directly at the viewer, creating a powerful and engaging image. The background is primarily green.

A close-up portrait of a young person's face looking upwards. The background is colorful, with the words "equidade" (equity), "igualdade" (equality), and "gente" (people) written in different fonts and colors. Use of bright colors and large text.

A stylized, elongated figure sitting with knees drawn up and arms resting on them. The figure is reading a book, with its face and the book illuminated by light. The background consists of a brick wall painted in shades of yellow and red. The word "ver" is written multiple times in a row.

Three figures holding up large banners. The central figure has an afro hairstyle. Each banner displays a significant word that together form "conviver" (to live together): "con" (with), "vive" (live), and "ver" (see). Below these words, additional text includes "cultura" (culture), "morada" (dwelling), and "memória" (memory). The background includes a sky with clouds and various abstract elements. Above the figures, a sign reads "Vila Itororó Canteiro Aberto".

A young child amidst a massive pile of garbage, with only their head and shoulders visible. Above the child, there's a painted face of a person with a serene and dreamy expression. Predominantly earthy tones and grays for the garbage, with vivid greens and light hues for the person's face.

Four children standing in a green field with a backdrop of urban buildings. Each child holds a sign with different messages. The signs read: "acesso a cultura" (access to culture), "mais amor por favor" (more love please), "a paternidade é a maior responsabilidade de um homem" (fatherhood is a person's greatest responsibility), and "queremos moradia digna" (we want decent housing). Bright colors like yellow, green, blue, and red.

A large portrait of a person with brown skin and short, curly hair, looking upwards with hands shielding their eyes from the sun, as if searching for something. Above the figure's head, the word "veracidade" (artists name) is written. Below the figure, the text reads "pode haver igualdade" (there can be equality).

A young child wearing a hat with a sun emblem and a red band, gazing directly at the viewer. To the left of the child, there is a chicken, and below the child, there is a small figure holding a heart. The background includes a rural landscape with a house and a field. The text reads "Todos somos migrantes" (We are all migrants).

An elderly person wearing a wide-brimmed hat, a colorful scarf, and a necklace of large yellow beads. They holds a sign that reads "58 pesos 8 horas" (58 pesos 8 hours). The background features a blue halo-like circle behind their head and a black backdrop with turquoise arrow patterns.

Three large, expressive faces of indigenous people. The central figure is a person with a mustache, flanked by two women, each wearing traditional hats adorned with green leaves. The backdrop is greenery, trees, and has small human silhouettes in black.

A portrait of a person of African descent. The individual is adorned with large, circular earrings and a prominent necklace made of spherical beads. They are wearing a red headdress and an orange garment. The background features tall, slender plants, possibly dandelions, and a small hut with a boat on a river at the bottom.

Two figures in a close, intimate pose. The figure on the left is depicted with tribal tattoos on the arm, a pink sleeveless top, and a facial expression with elements suggesting a cultural or historical theme. The figure on the right wears a brightly colored headdress featuring an owl motif and large beaded necklaces, reflecting indigenous or traditional attire. Both figures are set against a background with a cityscape and natural elements.

A large, older figure. They have a white beard, is wearing an orange robe with patterns, and has what appears to be a small animal on their head. Below them, a smaller human figure is riding a water buffalo, set against a landscape with green trees and a clear sky. The composition combines elements of both portraiture and landscape. Dominated by orange, green, and blue. The orange robe and the greenery of the landscape.

A row of individuals standing in line, each holding a plate or bowl. The focus is on their lower bodies and hands, which are positioned in a way that emphasizes the act of holding an empty dish. The artwork is rendered in black and white.

Mural, titled "O Sono dos Esquecidos" (The Sleep of the Forgotten), depicts a series of individuals sleeping on the street. Each figure is shown lying down with their belongings close by, capturing homelessness. The artwork is painted in muted tones of brown, black, and yellow, adding to the somber and reflective mood.

Two separate panels painted on an old, textured wall. The left panel, located inside a window frame, features a young person rendered in black and white with hints of green graffiti over them. They appears to be looking pensively to the side. The right panel, situated below what appears to be a door frame, shows a crouched person also depicted in black and white. The person is barefoot and dressed in simple clothing. Above them, the word "Clint" is written in red graffiti. The wall itself shows signs of weathering and decay.

On the left, in a window, a black and white depiction of a child gripping bars, with a distressed expression. In the center, below a door, a young girl, also in black and white, standing with their back against the wall and head. On the right, in a window, another child, also in black and white, is looking down with a somber expression. The image has graffiti elements, with the word "vagão" and other tags.

An elderly person with glasses and a hooded shawl, resting their arms on a ledge. Painted directly onto a rough stone wall. The background is shaded in grey tones, contrasting with the more detailed, white highlights used to define the person's features.
A person sleeping on the street, wrapped in a blanket, with a dog lying beside them. Use of monochromatic tones.
A person lying down, with a dog resting its head on their shoulder in a monochromatic style, using shades of grey, black, and white.

A person and a dog interacting. The person is positioned on the left side, and their face is close to the dog's face. The person appears to be holding the dog's head with one hand. The dog's head is tilted upwards. On the far left, there is another figure sitting with a dog lying down beside them. The entire scene is painted directly on a rough wall surface, with the figures blending into the texture of the wall. The mural extends along a sidewalk. The mural is painted using monochromatic shades of grey, black, and white.
A person sitting on the ground, dressed in a hooded jacket and beanie. There is graffiti text surrounding the figure. Colors: monochromatic shades of grey, black, and white.

Two children, depicted in black and white, sitting on the ground. The child on the left appears to be younger, while the one on the right is slightly older, possibly a girl. They are surrounded by dark shading. They are in front of an empty bowl. The primary colors are black, white, and grey, with turquoise graffiti lines around the children.

column4: Project: O FUTURO A OLHAR O PRESENTE
column7: Two children gripping barbed wire, their faces pressed close to it, with expressions of sadness. The mural is rendered in black and white. The child on the left, a boy, has spiky hair and large, sorrowful eyes, while the child on the right, a girl, also has large, expressive eyes. The barbed wire runs horizontally across the mural, symbolizing confinement and barriers.

column4: Project: O FUTURO A OLHAR O PRESENTE
column7: Four children behind barbed wire, their expressions filled with sadness and longing. The central figure, a child holding an empty bowl, looks directly at the viewer. The mural is rendered in black and white. The other children also have large, expressive eyes highlighting their vulnerability and need.

column4: Project: O FUTURO A OLHAR O PRESENTE
column7: Three children depicted behind barbed wire. The children’s faces are expressive, showing a range of emotions. The central figure has a solemn expression, while the figure on the right appears to have been injured, with blood depicted on their face and fingers. Use of red around the rightmost figure.

The image features three central elements: a malnourished child standing on the left with an outstretched hand as if begging, a bird behind vertical bars in the center, and a crouching person on the right who is covering their face with their hands, as if trying to prevent someone from approaching. The child on the left is dressed in torn clothing, emphasizing their thinness and frailty. The person on the right also wears tattered clothes, and their posture and hand placement suggest a sense of fear. The figures are depicted in black and white.

Three central figures. On the left, a person is siting. In the center, a person holds two empty bowls towards the viewer. On the right, a person looks into the distance, wearing a shackle around their neck symbolizing oppression or slavery. The mural is rendered in black and white.

The image depicts a person sleeping on the ground, with their head resting on their hand. Next to them lies a dog, also appearing to be at rest. The entire scene is rendered in black and white. On the right side of the image, the bare feet of another person, possibly a third individual, are visible. The artist's name, "@rosarlette_meirelles," is written at the top left of the image.

The top portion depicts a large pair of eyes, one of which has a tear falling, with a hand covering the mouth. Below, a person is shown lying on the ground. The entire mural is done in a monochromatic black and white palette.

Three figures: a young person writing, a person holding a book, and a partial figure on the left reaching upwards. Surrounding the central figure are various words in Portuguese such as "sonho" (dream), "curiosidade" (curiosity), and "liberdade" (freedom). The mural is painted in a monochromatic black and white palette, with a focus on the facial expressions and actions of the figures.
Three elderly people depicted in a realistic style, each with expressive faces and detailed features. The background is primarily blue, with colorful geometric shapes scattered around the figures.
